1
00:00:02,236 --> 00:00:05,239
[***]

2
00:01:14,342 --> 00:01:16,344
GANDALF:
 You cannot pass! 

3
00:01:16,344 --> 00:01:18,512
FRODO:
 Gandalf! 

4
00:01:22,850 --> 00:01:25,919
GANDALF: I am a servant 
 of the Secret Fire, 

5
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:28,522
 wielder of the flame of Anor. 

6
00:01:36,264 --> 00:01:39,800
 Go back to the Shadows. 

7
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:43,837
 The dark fire will not avail 
 you, flame of Udun! 

8
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:52,346
You shall not pass!

9
00:02:19,473 --> 00:02:21,175
No! No!

10
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:23,377
Gandalf!

11
00:02:30,851 --> 00:02:33,153
Fly, you fools.

12
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,223
No!

13
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:39,260
FRODO:
Gandalf!

14
00:02:55,409 --> 00:02:58,646
[BALROG GROWLS]

15
00:02:58,646 --> 00:03:00,881
[GANDALF YELLS]

16
00:03:47,828 --> 00:03:49,697
Gandalf!

17
00:03:50,498 --> 00:03:52,866
What is it, Mr. Frodo?

18
00:03:54,835 --> 00:03:56,604
Nothing.

19
00:04:03,844 --> 00:04:05,946
Just a dream.

20
00:04:21,629 --> 00:04:24,532
Mordor. The one place
in Middle-earth

21
00:04:24,532 --> 00:04:26,166
we don't want to see any closer.

22
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:29,303
And it's the one place
we're trying to get to.

23
00:04:29,303 --> 00:04:31,372
It's just where we can't get.

24
00:04:32,506 --> 00:04:35,709
Let's face it,
Mr. Frodo, we're lost.

25
00:04:37,711 --> 00:04:40,748
I don't think Gandalf meant
for us to come this way.

26
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:46,354
He didn't mean for a lot
of things to happen, Sam.

27
00:04:46,354 --> 00:04:47,988
But they did.

28
00:04:55,829 --> 00:04:57,465
[GROWLING]

29
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:02,069
Mr. Frodo?

30
00:05:05,973 --> 00:05:07,541
It's the Ring, isn't it?

31
00:05:08,376 --> 00:05:10,944
It's getting heavier.

32
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:25,258
What food have we got left?

33
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:26,326
Well, let me see.

34
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:29,162
Oh, yes. Lovely.

35
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:32,032
Lembas bread. And look!

36
00:05:34,368 --> 00:05:36,804
More lembas bread.

37
00:05:47,381 --> 00:05:49,016
I don't usually hold
with foreign food

38
00:05:49,016 --> 00:05:53,186
but this Elvish stuff,
it's not bad.

39
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:56,990
Nothing ever dampens your
spirits, does it, Sam?

40
00:06:02,663 --> 00:06:05,365
Those rain clouds might.

41
00:06:18,378 --> 00:06:20,113
This looks
strangely familiar.

42
00:06:21,649 --> 00:06:24,418
It's because we've
been here before.

43
00:06:24,418 --> 00:06:27,655
We're going in circles.

44
00:06:27,655 --> 00:06:29,690
SAM:
What is that horrid stink?

45
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:32,159
I warrant there's
a nasty bog nearby.

46
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:33,160
Can you smell it?

47
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,161
Yes.

48
00:06:36,163 --> 00:06:38,566
I can smell it.

49
00:06:41,569 --> 00:06:43,604
We're not alone.

50
00:06:57,651 --> 00:07:01,855
The thieves. The thieves.

51
00:07:01,855 --> 00:07:06,560
The filthy little thieves.

52
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,029
Where is it?

53
00:07:09,029 --> 00:07:12,332
Where is it?

54
00:07:12,332 --> 00:07:15,669
They stole it from us.

55
00:07:15,669 --> 00:07:20,708
My precious.

56
00:07:20,708 --> 00:07:24,077
Curse them, we hates them!

57
00:07:24,077 --> 00:07:28,616
It's ours, it is,
and we wants it!

58
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:25,372
This is Sting.

59
00:08:25,372 --> 00:08:27,140
You've seen it before,

60
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,810
haven't you, Gollum?

61
00:08:33,581 --> 00:08:37,250
Release him
or I'll cut your throat.

62
00:08:48,696 --> 00:08:53,233
[SCREAMING ECHOES]

63
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,202
It burns!

64
00:08:55,202 --> 00:08:57,638
It burns us!

65
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:00,608
It freezes!

66
00:09:02,242 --> 00:09:04,578
Nasty Elves twisted it.

67
00:09:04,578 --> 00:09:06,346
Take it off us!

68
00:09:06,346 --> 00:09:07,581
Quiet, you!

69
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,885
It's hopeless.

70
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:14,855
Every Orc in Mordor's going
to hear this racket.

71
00:09:14,855 --> 00:09:16,556
Let's just tie him up
and leave him.

72
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:17,891
No!

73
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,627
That would kill us!

74
00:09:19,627 --> 00:09:21,561
Kill us!

75
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,732
It's no more than you deserve!

76
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:28,235
Maybe he does deserve to die.

77
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:34,074
But now that I see him,
I do pity him.

78
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:42,515
We be nice to them
if they be nice to us.

79
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:45,318
Take it off us.

80
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:52,492
We swears to do what you wants.

81
00:09:52,492 --> 00:09:54,327
We swears.

82
00:09:54,327 --> 00:09:57,230
There's no promise you can make
that I can trust.

83
00:09:59,767 --> 00:10:01,769
We swears,

84
00:10:01,769 --> 00:10:04,604
to serve the master

85
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,774
of the precious.

86
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:10,844
We will swear on...

87
00:10:10,844 --> 00:10:12,780
On the precious!

88
00:10:12,780 --> 00:10:15,082
Gollum. Gollum.

89
00:10:15,082 --> 00:10:20,253
The Ring is treacherous.
It will hold you to your word.

90
00:10:20,253 --> 00:10:21,989
Yes...

91
00:10:21,989 --> 00:10:24,792
...on the precious.

92
00:10:27,094 --> 00:10:29,629
On the precious.

93
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:32,232
I don't believe you!

94
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:36,303
Get down! I said, down!

95
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:37,738
Sam!

96
00:10:37,738 --> 00:10:39,439
He's trying to trick us.

97
00:10:39,439 --> 00:10:42,943
If we let him go,
he'll throttle us in our sleep.

98
00:10:54,021 --> 00:10:56,089
You know the way to Mordor?

99
00:10:56,089 --> 00:10:58,859
Yes.

100
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:04,331
You've been there before?

101
00:11:04,331 --> 00:11:06,133
Yes.

102
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:19,713
You will lead us
to the Black Gate.

103
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,736
Merry!

104
00:11:42,736 --> 00:11:44,404
Merry!

105
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:50,277
What is it? What do you smell?

106
00:11:50,277 --> 00:11:51,378
Man-flesh.

107
00:11:51,378 --> 00:11:54,581
Aragorn.

108
00:11:54,581 --> 00:11:57,184
They've picked up our trail.

109
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:59,152
Let's move!

110
00:12:20,808 --> 00:12:23,443
Their pace has quickened.

111
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:26,546
They must have caught our scent.

112
00:12:26,546 --> 00:12:28,348
Hurry!

113
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:33,887
Come on, Gimli!

114
00:12:37,524 --> 00:12:39,893
Three days and nights pursuit.

115
00:12:39,893 --> 00:12:42,830
No food. No rest.

116
00:12:42,830 --> 00:12:47,234
And no sign of our quarry,
but what bare rock can tell.

117
00:13:18,365 --> 00:13:21,935
Not idly do
the leaves of Lorien fall.

118
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:26,173
They may yet be alive.

119
00:13:26,173 --> 00:13:29,142
Less than a day
ahead of us. Come.

120
00:13:31,344 --> 00:13:34,081
Come, Gimli!
We're gaining on them!

121
00:13:34,081 --> 00:13:36,016
I'm wasted on cross-country.

122
00:13:36,016 --> 00:13:38,418
We Dwarves
are natural sprinters.

123
00:13:38,418 --> 00:13:42,522
Very dangerous
over short distances.

124
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,869
Rohan.

125
00:13:55,869 --> 00:13:58,906
Home of the Horse-lords.

126
00:13:58,906 --> 00:14:02,475
There's something
strange at work here.

127
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:05,778
Some evil gives speed
to these creatures.

128
00:14:05,778 --> 00:14:08,949
Sets its will against us.

129
00:14:13,753 --> 00:14:16,990
ARAGORN: Legolas!
What do your Elf-eyes see?

130
00:14:16,990 --> 00:14:19,526
The Uruks turn northeast.

131
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:22,729
They are taking
the Hobbits to Isengard.

132
00:14:22,729 --> 00:14:24,998
Saruman.

133
00:14:26,599 --> 00:14:29,502
[METAL CLANGING]

134
00:14:33,073 --> 00:14:36,376
SARUMAN:
 The world is changing. 

135
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:40,447
 Who now has the strength 
 to stand against the armies 

136
00:14:40,447 --> 00:14:42,782
 of Isengard 

137
00:14:42,782 --> 00:14:45,618
 and Mordor? 

138
00:14:47,154 --> 00:14:52,993
 To stand against the might 
 of Sauron and Saruman 

139
00:14:52,993 --> 00:14:56,896
 and the union 
 of the two towers? 

140
00:15:03,103 --> 00:15:06,206
 Together, my Lord Sauron 

141
00:15:06,206 --> 00:15:10,043
 we shall rule 
 this Middle-earth. 

142
00:15:10,978 --> 00:15:14,014
[GROWLING AND SCREECHING]

143
00:15:25,692 --> 00:15:30,763
 The Old World will burn 
 in the fires of industry. 

144
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:34,167
 The forests will fall. 

145
00:15:35,902 --> 00:15:38,671
 A new order will rise. 

146
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:43,210
 We will drive the machine 
 of war with the sword 

147
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:49,082
 and the spear 
 and the iron fists of the Orc. 

148
00:15:57,857 --> 00:16:03,596
 We have only to remove 
 those who oppose us. 

149
00:16:04,397 --> 00:16:06,533
The Horse-Men took your lands.

150
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:09,202
They drove your people
into the hills

151
00:16:09,202 --> 00:16:11,438
to scratch a living off rocks.

152
00:16:11,438 --> 00:16:13,573
Murderers!

153
00:16:13,573 --> 00:16:16,009
Take back the lands
they stole from you.

154
00:16:16,009 --> 00:16:18,045
Burn every village!

155
00:16:24,517 --> 00:16:27,787
SARUMAN:
 It will begin in Rohan. 

156
00:16:27,787 --> 00:16:31,724
 Too long have these peasants 
 stood against you. 

157
00:16:31,724 --> 00:16:33,726
 But no more. 

158
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:36,129
Eothain! Eothain!

159
00:16:37,864 --> 00:16:41,101
You take your sister.
You'll go faster with just two.

160
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,970
Papa says Eothain
must not ride Garulf.

161
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:45,738
He is too big for him.

162
00:16:45,738 --> 00:16:47,140
Listen to me.

163
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:48,975
You must ride to Edoras
and raise the alarm.

164
00:16:48,975 --> 00:16:50,143
Do you understand me?

165
00:16:50,143 --> 00:16:51,611
Yes, Mama.

166
00:16:51,611 --> 00:16:54,881
I don't want to leave.
I don't want to go, Mama.

167
00:16:54,881 --> 00:16:57,917
Freda, I will find you there.

168
00:16:57,917 --> 00:16:59,752
[SCREAMING]

169
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:05,024
Quickly!

170
00:17:11,664 --> 00:17:13,333
Go, child.

171
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:26,379
SARUMAN:
 Rohan, my lord 

172
00:17:26,379 --> 00:17:28,315
 is ready to fall. 

173
00:17:53,706 --> 00:17:54,774
Theodred.

174
00:18:08,888 --> 00:18:12,225
EOWYN: Your son
is badly wounded, my lord.

175
00:18:12,225 --> 00:18:15,295
He was ambushed by Orcs.

176
00:18:16,463 --> 00:18:20,233
If we don't defend our country,
Saruman will take it by force.

177
00:18:20,233 --> 00:18:23,270
That is a lie.

178
00:18:25,037 --> 00:18:30,377
Saruman the White has ever been
our friend and ally.

179
00:18:31,844 --> 00:18:33,846
Grima.

180
00:18:35,182 --> 00:18:37,317
Grima.

181
00:18:39,752 --> 00:18:41,788
Grima.

182
00:18:41,788 --> 00:18:45,392
Orcs are roaming freely
across our lands.

183
00:18:45,392 --> 00:18:48,928
Unchecked. Unchallenged.
Killing at will.

184
00:18:48,928 --> 00:18:52,732
Orcs bearing
the White Hand of Saruman.

185
00:19:00,407 --> 00:19:06,346
Why do you lay these troubles
on an already troubled mind?

186
00:19:06,346 --> 00:19:08,848
Can you not see?

187
00:19:08,848 --> 00:19:14,254
Your uncle is wearied
by your malcontent,

188
00:19:14,254 --> 00:19:16,923
your warmongering.

189
00:19:19,025 --> 00:19:20,960
Warmongering?

190
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,363
How long is it since
Saruman bought you?

191
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:26,533
What was
the promised price, Grima?

192
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:27,867
When all the Men are dead,

193
00:19:27,867 --> 00:19:29,569
you will take your share
of the treasure?

194
00:19:42,715 --> 00:19:45,585
Too long have
you watched my sister.

195
00:19:45,585 --> 00:19:47,820
Too long have
you haunted her steps.

196
00:19:55,595 --> 00:20:00,233
You see much, Eomer,
son of Eomund.

197
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:01,568
Too much.

198
00:20:03,636 --> 00:20:06,539
You are banished forthwith

199
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:09,809
from the kingdom of Rohan

200
00:20:09,809 --> 00:20:12,279
under pain of death.

201
00:20:21,521 --> 00:20:24,957
[***]

202
00:20:43,042 --> 00:20:45,978
Keep breathing. That's the key.

203
00:20:45,978 --> 00:20:47,814
Breathe.

204
00:20:51,651 --> 00:20:52,952
They've run as if the very whips

205
00:20:52,952 --> 00:20:55,722
of their masters
were behind them.

206
00:21:11,671 --> 00:21:13,773
We're not going no further

207
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:16,108
until we've had a breather.

208
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:18,678
Get a fire going!

209
00:21:22,682 --> 00:21:24,617
Merry!

210
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:25,885
Merry!

211
00:21:27,454 --> 00:21:31,023
I think we might
have made a mistake

212
00:21:31,023 --> 00:21:32,859
leaving the Shire, Pippin.

213
00:21:38,164 --> 00:21:42,168
[TREES GROANING]

214
00:21:42,168 --> 00:21:44,537
What's making that noise?

215
00:21:46,005 --> 00:21:47,440
It's the trees.

216
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,108
What?

217
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:53,480
You remember the Old Forest,
on the borders of Buckland?

218
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,482
Folk used to say there was
something in the water

219
00:21:55,482 --> 00:21:58,485
that made the trees grow tall

220
00:21:58,485 --> 00:21:59,919
and come alive.

221
00:21:59,919 --> 00:22:02,489
Alive?

222
00:22:02,489 --> 00:22:04,457
Trees that could whisper,

223
00:22:05,257 --> 00:22:07,960
talk to each other,

224
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,896
even move.

225
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:13,666
I'm starving.

226
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:18,204
We ain't had nothing but maggoty
bread for three stinking days.

227
00:22:18,204 --> 00:22:19,606
Yeah!

228
00:22:19,606 --> 00:22:23,410
Why can't we have some meat?!

229
00:22:25,311 --> 00:22:27,814
What about them?

230
00:22:27,814 --> 00:22:30,249
They're fresh.

231
00:22:30,249 --> 00:22:33,386
They are not for eating.

232
00:22:40,059 --> 00:22:42,161
What about their legs?

233
00:22:42,161 --> 00:22:44,631
They don't need those.

234
00:22:45,765 --> 00:22:47,467
Ooh, they look tasty.

235
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:49,402
Get back, scum!

236
00:22:50,837 --> 00:22:51,838
Carve them up!

237
00:22:51,838 --> 00:22:53,372
Just a mouthful.

238
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:55,074
No!

239
00:22:56,876 --> 00:23:00,780
Looks like meat's back
on the menu, boys.

240
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,555
Pippin.

241
00:23:08,555 --> 00:23:10,523
Let's go.

242
00:23:18,865 --> 00:23:20,399
Go on.

243
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:22,068
Call for help.

244
00:23:23,302 --> 00:23:24,471
Squeal.

245
00:23:24,471 --> 00:23:27,940
No one's going to save you now.

246
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:33,012
[HORSE WHINNIES]

247
00:23:37,083 --> 00:23:38,618
Pippin!

248
00:24:02,609 --> 00:24:05,612
A red sun rises.

249
00:24:05,612 --> 00:24:07,814
Blood has
been spilled this night.

250
00:24:39,746 --> 00:24:42,181
Riders of Rohan,

251
00:24:42,181 --> 00:24:44,717
what news from the Mark?

252
00:25:12,311 --> 00:25:13,913
What business does an Elf,

253
00:25:13,913 --> 00:25:16,716
a Man and a Dwarf have
in the Riddermark?

254
00:25:16,716 --> 00:25:18,585
Speak quickly!

255
00:25:18,585 --> 00:25:23,923
Give me your name, horse-master,
and I shall give you mine.

256
00:25:32,799 --> 00:25:35,334
I would cut off your head,
Dwarf,

257
00:25:35,334 --> 00:25:39,138
if it stood but a little higher
from the ground.

258
00:25:39,138 --> 00:25:41,608
You would die before
your stroke fell.

259
00:25:49,949 --> 00:25:52,351
I am Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

260
00:25:52,351 --> 00:25:54,220
This is Gimli, son of Gloin,

261
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:56,455
and Legolas
of the Woodland Realm.

262
00:25:56,455 --> 00:26:00,092
We are friends of Rohan
and of Theoden, your king.

263
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:05,598
Theoden no longer recognizes
friend from foe.

264
00:26:05,598 --> 00:26:08,034
Not even his own kin.

265
00:26:12,171 --> 00:26:14,273
Saruman has poisoned the mind
of the king

266
00:26:14,273 --> 00:26:16,676
and claimed lordship
over these lands.

267
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:21,547
My company
are those loyal to Rohan.

268
00:26:21,547 --> 00:26:23,616
And for that, we are banished.

269
00:26:25,417 --> 00:26:29,188
The White Wizard is cunning.

270
00:26:29,188 --> 00:26:31,791
He walks here
and there, they say,

271
00:26:31,791 --> 00:26:34,126
as an old man hooded
and cloaked.

272
00:26:35,795 --> 00:26:39,699
And everywhere, his spies
slip past our nets.

273
00:26:39,699 --> 00:26:42,001
We are no spies.

274
00:26:42,001 --> 00:26:45,271
We track a party of Uruk-hai
westward across the plain.

275
00:26:45,271 --> 00:26:48,574
They have taken two
of our friends captive.

276
00:26:48,574 --> 00:26:50,009
The Uruks are destroyed.

277
00:26:50,009 --> 00:26:51,711
We slaughtered
them during the night.

278
00:26:51,711 --> 00:26:52,879
But there were two Hobbits.

279
00:26:52,879 --> 00:26:54,346
Did you see two
Hobbits with them?

280
00:26:54,346 --> 00:26:57,784
They would be small.
Only children to your eyes.

281
00:27:00,787 --> 00:27:03,155
We left none alive.

282
00:27:03,155 --> 00:27:05,858
We piled the carcasses
and burned them.

283
00:27:12,031 --> 00:27:13,265
Dead?

284
00:27:16,235 --> 00:27:17,303
I am sorry.

285
00:27:22,441 --> 00:27:23,442
[WHISTLING]

286
00:27:23,442 --> 00:27:25,878
Hasufel! Arod!

287
00:27:27,313 --> 00:27:30,449
May these horses bear you
to better fortune

288
00:27:30,449 --> 00:27:32,251
than their former masters.

289
00:27:33,485 --> 00:27:35,154
Farewell.

290
00:27:40,292 --> 00:27:42,862
Look for your friends.

291
00:27:42,862 --> 00:27:45,264
But do not trust to hope.

292
00:27:46,799 --> 00:27:49,635
It has forsaken these lands.

293
00:27:49,635 --> 00:27:51,838
We ride north!

294
00:28:42,121 --> 00:28:44,290
It's one of their wee belts.

295
00:28:44,290 --> 00:28:45,324
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

296
00:28:51,998 --> 00:28:54,133
Ahh!

297
00:28:57,837 --> 00:29:00,106
We failed them.

298
00:29:13,886 --> 00:29:16,222
A Hobbit lay here.

299
00:29:17,957 --> 00:29:19,859
And the other.

300
00:29:30,502 --> 00:29:32,238
They crawled.

301
00:29:36,108 --> 00:29:38,377
Their hands were bound.

302
00:29:50,522 --> 00:29:51,858
Their bonds were cut.

303
00:30:07,739 --> 00:30:10,042
They ran over here.

304
00:30:13,412 --> 00:30:14,981
They were followed.

305
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:19,886
MERRY: The belt!

306
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:24,891
MERRY: Run!

307
00:30:28,227 --> 00:30:29,929
Tracks lead away
from the battle...

308
00:30:34,633 --> 00:30:36,568
into Fangorn Forest.

309
00:30:37,636 --> 00:30:39,071
Fangorn?

310
00:30:39,071 --> 00:30:42,041
What madness
drove them in there?

311
00:30:59,358 --> 00:31:02,628
PIPPIN:
Did we lose him?
I think we lost him.

312
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:05,932
[SNARLING
AND BRANCHES SNAPPING]

313
00:31:09,135 --> 00:31:12,939
I'm going to rip out
your filthy little innards!

314
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:20,112
Come here!

315
00:31:25,484 --> 00:31:28,187
Trees. Climb a tree.

316
00:31:37,396 --> 00:31:39,231
He's gone.

317
00:31:44,770 --> 00:31:45,972
[GRUNTS]

318
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:53,579
Merry!

319
00:31:54,913 --> 00:31:57,516
[GROANS]

320
00:32:04,256 --> 00:32:05,224
[YELLS]

321
00:32:05,224 --> 00:32:09,461
Let's put a maggot hole
in your belly!

322
00:32:16,502 --> 00:32:18,204
Run, Merry!

323
00:32:23,742 --> 00:32:25,277
[GRUNTING]

324
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:31,483
Little Orcs,
bru-ra-hroom.

325
00:32:31,483 --> 00:32:34,786
It's talking, Merry.
The tree is talking.

326
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,822
Tree?

327
00:32:36,822 --> 00:32:39,992
I am no tree!

328
00:32:39,992 --> 00:32:42,494
I am an Ent.

329
00:32:42,494 --> 00:32:45,064
A tree-herder.

330
00:32:45,064 --> 00:32:47,166
A shepherd of the forest.

331
00:32:47,166 --> 00:32:49,068
Don't talk to it, Merry.

332
00:32:49,068 --> 00:32:50,802
Don't encourage it!

333
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:55,107
Treebeard, some call me.

334
00:32:55,107 --> 00:32:57,776
And whose side are you on?

335
00:32:57,776 --> 00:32:59,645
Side?

336
00:32:59,645 --> 00:33:02,648
I am on nobody's side...

337
00:33:02,648 --> 00:33:08,954
because nobody's on my side,
little Orc.

338
00:33:08,954 --> 00:33:13,792
Nobody cares
for the woods anymore.

339
00:33:13,792 --> 00:33:16,595
We're not Orcs!
We're Hobbits!

340
00:33:16,595 --> 00:33:19,098
Hobbits? Hmm.

341
00:33:20,032 --> 00:33:25,171
Never heard
of a Hobbit before.

342
00:33:26,105 --> 00:33:28,607
Sounds like
Orc mischief to me!

343
00:33:28,607 --> 00:33:30,842
[GRIP TIGHTENING]

344
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,145
They come with fire.

345
00:33:33,145 --> 00:33:35,781
They come with axes.

346
00:33:35,781 --> 00:33:40,786
Gnawing, biting, breaking,
hacking, burning!

347
00:33:40,786 --> 00:33:43,622
Destroyers and usurpers!
Curse them!

348
00:33:43,622 --> 00:33:44,890
No!

349
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:49,195
You don't understand.
We're Hobbits! Halflings!

350
00:33:49,995 --> 00:33:51,230
Shire-folk!

351
00:33:51,230 --> 00:33:53,932
Maybe you are...

352
00:33:53,932 --> 00:33:58,304
and maybe you aren't.

353
00:33:58,304 --> 00:34:02,774
The White Wizard will know.

354
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:04,810
The White Wizard?

355
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:08,514
Saruman.

356
00:34:20,926 --> 00:34:22,828
See? See?

357
00:34:22,828 --> 00:34:25,297
We've led you out.

358
00:34:25,297 --> 00:34:28,167
Hurry, Hobbitses.
Hurry!

359
00:34:30,969 --> 00:34:33,672
Very lucky
we find you.

360
00:34:40,146 --> 00:34:42,181
Nice Hobbit.

361
00:34:43,815 --> 00:34:44,850
[SAM YELLS]

362
00:34:44,850 --> 00:34:47,018
It's a bog.

363
00:34:47,018 --> 00:34:48,220
He's led us
into a swamp.

364
00:34:48,220 --> 00:34:51,290
A swamp, yes, yes.

365
00:34:51,290 --> 00:34:56,562
Come, master. We will take you
on safe paths through the mist.

366
00:34:58,530 --> 00:35:02,368
Come, Hobbits! Come!
We go quickly.

367
00:35:05,304 --> 00:35:08,174
GOLLUM:
I found it. I did.

368
00:35:08,174 --> 00:35:10,876
The way through the marshes.

369
00:35:10,876 --> 00:35:14,646
Orcs don't use it.
Orcs don't know it.

370
00:35:14,646 --> 00:35:19,050
They go around
for miles and miles.

371
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:20,552
Come quickly.

372
00:35:20,552 --> 00:35:24,856
Soft and quick as shadows
we must be.

373
00:35:41,873 --> 00:35:43,875
There are dead things!

374
00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:45,744
Dead faces in the water.

375
00:35:50,382 --> 00:35:55,020
All dead.
All rotten.

376
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:58,924
Elves and Men
and Orcses.

377
00:35:58,924 --> 00:36:03,295
A great battle long ago.

378
00:36:03,295 --> 00:36:05,231
Dead Marshes.

379
00:36:05,231 --> 00:36:08,267
Yes. Yes, that is their name.

380
00:36:09,768 --> 00:36:11,503
This way.

381
00:36:11,503 --> 00:36:14,640
Don't follow the lights.

382
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,941
[GRUNTS]

383
00:36:15,941 --> 00:36:19,978
Careful now! Or Hobbits go down
to join the dead ones

384
00:36:19,978 --> 00:36:24,516
and light little candles
of their own.

385
00:36:27,919 --> 00:36:30,589
[VOICES WHISPERING AND WAILING]

386
00:36:50,175 --> 00:36:51,410
Frodo!

387
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:31,583
[PANTING AND GRUNTING]

388
00:37:36,355 --> 00:37:37,389
Gollum?

389
00:37:37,389 --> 00:37:41,293
Don't follow the lights.

390
00:37:41,293 --> 00:37:43,329
Gollum!
Mr. Frodo!

391
00:37:43,329 --> 00:37:45,464
Are you all right?

392
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:49,868
[RUMBLING]

393
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:17,262
So bright.

394
00:38:17,262 --> 00:38:21,232
So beautiful.

395
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:25,371
Our precious.

396
00:38:26,472 --> 00:38:28,239
What did you say?

397
00:38:28,239 --> 00:38:30,576
Master should be resting.

398
00:38:30,576 --> 00:38:34,880
Master needs to keep up
his strength.

399
00:38:36,782 --> 00:38:37,749
Who are you?

400
00:38:37,749 --> 00:38:40,151
Mustn't ask us.
Not its business.

401
00:38:40,151 --> 00:38:41,687
Gollum. Gollum.

402
00:38:41,687 --> 00:38:43,655
Gandalf told me you were
one of the river-folk.

403
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:45,624
* Cold be heart
And hand and bone *

404
00:38:45,624 --> 00:38:47,859
* Cold be travelers
Far from home *

405
00:38:47,859 --> 00:38:49,695
He said your life
was a sad story.

406
00:38:49,695 --> 00:38:51,930
* They do not see
What lies ahead *

407
00:38:51,930 --> 00:38:54,265
* When sun has failed
And moon is dead **

408
00:38:54,265 --> 00:38:57,803
You were not so very different
from a Hobbit once.

409
00:38:57,803 --> 00:38:59,671
Were you?

410
00:39:01,773 --> 00:39:04,009
Smeagol.

411
00:39:08,514 --> 00:39:11,383
What did you call me?

412
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:19,057
A long time ago.

413
00:39:19,057 --> 00:39:21,427
My name.

414
00:39:22,227 --> 00:39:23,895
My name.

415
00:39:27,332 --> 00:39:29,000
S...

416
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,769
S...

417
00:39:30,769 --> 00:39:33,238
Smeagol.

418
00:39:33,238 --> 00:39:34,940
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHES]

419
00:39:35,974 --> 00:39:36,975
[YELLS]

420
00:39:36,975 --> 00:39:39,110
Black Riders!

421
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:40,479
Hide! Hide!

422
00:39:41,279 --> 00:39:43,449
[YELLS]

423
00:39:50,822 --> 00:39:53,191
Come on, Frodo. Come on!

424
00:39:53,191 --> 00:39:57,729
GOLLUM:
Quick! They will see us!
They will see us!

425
00:39:57,729 --> 00:39:59,130
I thought they were dead.

426
00:39:59,130 --> 00:40:00,599
Dead?

427
00:40:00,599 --> 00:40:03,669
No, you cannot kill them. No.

428
00:40:03,669 --> 00:40:05,804
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHES]

429
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:11,109
[SNIFFING]

430
00:40:27,526 --> 00:40:29,427
[YELLS
AND RINGWRAITH SCREECHES]

431
00:40:30,896 --> 00:40:32,130
Wraiths!

432
00:40:32,130 --> 00:40:34,533
Wraiths on wings!

433
00:40:37,769 --> 00:40:40,005
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHES]

434
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:44,476
They are calling for it.

435
00:40:44,476 --> 00:40:48,179
They are calling
for the precious.

436
00:40:50,215 --> 00:40:52,450
Mr. Frodo! It's all right.

437
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:53,919
I'm here.

438
00:40:55,053 --> 00:40:56,555
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHES]

439
00:41:01,527 --> 00:41:03,662
[FELL BEAST ROARS]

440
00:41:09,668 --> 00:41:11,737
Hurry, Hobbits.

441
00:41:11,737 --> 00:41:15,941
The Black Gate is very close.

442
00:41:21,046 --> 00:41:22,614
[SNIFFS AND SPITS]

443
00:41:22,614 --> 00:41:24,750
Orc blood.

444
00:41:34,492 --> 00:41:36,562
These are strange tracks.

445
00:41:37,529 --> 00:41:39,865
The air is so close in here.

446
00:41:40,666 --> 00:41:44,035
This forest is old.

447
00:41:44,035 --> 00:41:46,104
Very old.

448
00:41:47,639 --> 00:41:50,141
Full of memory...

449
00:41:50,141 --> 00:41:52,578
[TREES GROANING]

450
00:41:52,578 --> 00:41:54,946
and anger.

451
00:41:54,946 --> 00:41:56,682
[CREAKING]

452
00:42:00,986 --> 00:42:04,255
The trees are speaking
to each other.

453
00:42:04,255 --> 00:42:05,356
Gimli!

454
00:42:05,356 --> 00:42:07,192
Lower your ax.

455
00:42:08,293 --> 00:42:09,861
Oh.

456
00:42:13,264 --> 00:42:14,399
Aragorn,

457
00:42:14,399 --> 00:42:15,967
[IN ELVISH]

458
00:42:24,676 --> 00:42:27,312
The White Wizard
approaches.

459
00:42:33,151 --> 00:42:37,856
Do not let him speak.
He will put a spell on us.

460
00:42:47,165 --> 00:42:49,601
We must be quick.

461
00:42:53,271 --> 00:42:54,272
[YELLS]

462
00:43:04,716 --> 00:43:08,787
WHITE WIZARD:
You are tracking the footsteps
of two young Hobbits.

463
00:43:08,787 --> 00:43:10,155
Where are they?

464
00:43:11,122 --> 00:43:14,592
They passed this way
the day before yesterday.

465
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:18,930
They met someone
they did not expect.

466
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:20,666
Does that comfort you?

467
00:43:20,666 --> 00:43:22,333
Who are you?

468
00:43:24,736 --> 00:43:26,237
Show yourself!

469
00:43:35,613 --> 00:43:37,883
It cannot be.

470
00:43:47,058 --> 00:43:48,694
You fell.

471
00:43:49,828 --> 00:43:52,597
Through fire...

472
00:43:52,597 --> 00:43:54,065
and water.

473
00:43:55,200 --> 00:43:57,969
 From the lowest dungeon 
 to the highest peak, 

474
00:43:57,969 --> 00:44:02,040
 I fought with the Balrog 
 of Morgoth. 

475
00:44:12,851 --> 00:44:15,020
[BALROG GRUNTS]

476
00:44:17,455 --> 00:44:20,358
 Until at last I threw down 
 my enemy, 

477
00:44:20,358 --> 00:44:25,196
 and smote his ruin 
 upon the mountainside. 

478
00:44:30,869 --> 00:44:34,205
 Darkness took me, 

479
00:44:34,205 --> 00:44:39,077
 and I strayed out of thought 
 and time. 

480
00:44:39,077 --> 00:44:42,347
 Stars wheeled overhead, 

481
00:44:42,347 --> 00:44:47,185
 and every day was as long 
 as a life age of the Earth. 

482
00:44:49,054 --> 00:44:51,556
 But it was not the end. 

483
00:44:51,556 --> 00:44:54,793
 I felt life in me again. 

484
00:44:54,793 --> 00:44:56,361
[GASPS]

485
00:44:56,361 --> 00:44:58,930
 I've been sent back, 

486
00:44:58,930 --> 00:45:00,698
until my task is done.

487
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:02,467
Gandalf.

488
00:45:03,568 --> 00:45:06,104
Gandalf?

489
00:45:06,104 --> 00:45:08,006
Yes.

490
00:45:10,575 --> 00:45:12,443
That was what
they used to call me.

491
00:45:15,313 --> 00:45:17,783
Gandalf the Grey.

492
00:45:18,784 --> 00:45:20,718
That was my name.

493
00:45:20,718 --> 00:45:22,320
Gandalf.

494
00:45:24,055 --> 00:45:26,357
I am Gandalf the White.

495
00:45:29,127 --> 00:45:32,530
And I come back to you now...

496
00:45:32,530 --> 00:45:34,866
at the turn of the tide.

497
00:45:34,866 --> 00:45:38,369
GANDALF:
One stage of your journey
is over. Another begins.

498
00:45:38,369 --> 00:45:39,905
War has come to Rohan.

499
00:45:39,905 --> 00:45:42,808
We must ride to Edoras
with all speed.

500
00:45:42,808 --> 00:45:44,342
[WHISTLING]

501
00:45:53,985 --> 00:45:56,321
[SHADOWFAX NEIGHS]

502
00:46:04,796 --> 00:46:06,297
That is one of the Mearas,

503
00:46:06,297 --> 00:46:09,367
unless my eyes are cheated
by some spell.

504
00:46:26,818 --> 00:46:29,287
GANDALF: Shadowfax.

505
00:46:31,656 --> 00:46:34,459
He is the lord of all horses...

506
00:46:35,894 --> 00:46:40,098
and has been my friend
through many dangers.

507
00:46:54,345 --> 00:46:58,850
TREEBEARD:
 My home lies deep 
 in the forest 

508
00:46:58,850 --> 00:47:03,021
 near the roots of the mountain. 

509
00:47:05,090 --> 00:47:08,860
I told Gandalf
I would keep you safe.

510
00:47:08,860 --> 00:47:12,463
And safe is where I'll keep you.

511
00:47:13,398 --> 00:47:17,869
The trees have grown wild
and dangerous.

512
00:47:17,869 --> 00:47:21,139
Anger festers in their hearts.

513
00:47:21,139 --> 00:47:23,942
They will harm you if they can.

514
00:47:23,942 --> 00:47:28,013
There are too few of us now.

515
00:47:28,013 --> 00:47:33,118
Too few of us Ents
left to manage them.

516
00:47:40,825 --> 00:47:44,529
GOLLUM:
The Black Gate of Mordor.

517
00:47:48,566 --> 00:47:51,202
Oh, save us.

518
00:47:56,507 --> 00:47:58,876
My old Gaffer would have
a thing or two to say

519
00:47:58,876 --> 00:48:00,211
if he could see us now.

520
00:48:02,147 --> 00:48:06,684
Master says to show him
the way into Mordor.

521
00:48:07,518 --> 00:48:10,555
So good Smeagol does,
master says so.

522
00:48:10,555 --> 00:48:11,990
I did.

523
00:48:20,531 --> 00:48:22,633
That's it, then.

524
00:48:24,002 --> 00:48:25,370
We can't get past that.

525
00:48:25,370 --> 00:48:29,040
[EASTERLINGS
YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

526
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:34,112
[YELLING AND DRUMMING]

527
00:48:36,647 --> 00:48:39,517
[HORN BLOWS]

528
00:48:41,786 --> 00:48:44,555
[BLOWS HORN]

529
00:48:48,859 --> 00:48:50,561
[SCREECHES]

530
00:49:10,615 --> 00:49:12,017
Look!

531
00:49:12,017 --> 00:49:13,718
The gate.

532
00:49:13,718 --> 00:49:15,153
It's opening!

533
00:49:22,227 --> 00:49:24,562
I can see
a way down.

534
00:49:24,562 --> 00:49:25,963
Sam, no!

535
00:49:25,963 --> 00:49:27,698
[YELLS]

536
00:49:29,434 --> 00:49:30,968
Master!

537
00:49:39,444 --> 00:49:41,379
[ROCKS FALLING]

538
00:50:42,873 --> 00:50:44,742
[DRUMMING]

539
00:50:47,178 --> 00:50:49,147
[EASTERLINGS
YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

540
00:50:54,219 --> 00:50:56,254
I do not ask you
to come with me, Sam.

541
00:50:56,254 --> 00:50:58,656
I know, Mr. Frodo.

542
00:50:58,656 --> 00:51:02,127
I doubt even these Elvish cloaks
will hide us in there.

543
00:51:02,127 --> 00:51:03,394
Now!

544
00:51:03,394 --> 00:51:04,862
No!

545
00:51:04,862 --> 00:51:06,997
No! No, master!

546
00:51:06,997 --> 00:51:10,268
They catch you!
They catch you!

547
00:51:11,202 --> 00:51:14,139
Don't take it to him.

548
00:51:16,807 --> 00:51:19,544
He wants the precious.

549
00:51:19,544 --> 00:51:22,713
Always he is looking for it.

550
00:51:22,713 --> 00:51:27,017
And the precious is wanting
to go back to him.

551
00:51:27,017 --> 00:51:31,189
But we mustn't
let him have it.

552
00:51:37,228 --> 00:51:39,497
No! There's another way.

553
00:51:39,497 --> 00:51:42,367
More secret.
A dark way.

554
00:51:42,367 --> 00:51:44,535
Why haven't you spoken
of this before?

555
00:51:44,535 --> 00:51:46,337
Because master
did not ask.

556
00:51:46,337 --> 00:51:47,772
He's up to something.

557
00:51:47,772 --> 00:51:50,241
Are you saying there's
another way into Mordor?

558
00:51:50,241 --> 00:51:54,078
Yes. There's a path,

559
00:51:54,078 --> 00:51:56,847
and some stairs.

560
00:51:56,847 --> 00:51:57,982
And then...

561
00:51:57,982 --> 00:52:02,119
a tunnel.

562
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:04,689
[GATE CREAKING]

563
00:52:15,966 --> 00:52:17,935
He's led us this far, Sam.

564
00:52:17,935 --> 00:52:19,504
Mr. Frodo, no.

565
00:52:20,371 --> 00:52:22,207
He's been true to his word.

566
00:52:26,844 --> 00:52:28,246
No.

567
00:52:30,114 --> 00:52:31,949
Lead the way, Smeagol.

568
00:52:31,949 --> 00:52:36,487
Good Smeagol always helps.

569
00:52:46,431 --> 00:52:48,899
[GATES CLANG SHUT]

570
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:06,717
GANDALF:
Edoras and the Golden Hall
of Meduseld.

571
00:53:06,717 --> 00:53:10,255
There dwells Theoden,
King of Rohan,

572
00:53:10,255 --> 00:53:13,724
 whose mind is overthrown. 

573
00:53:13,724 --> 00:53:15,860
 Saruman's hold over 
 King Theoden 

574
00:53:15,860 --> 00:53:18,663
 is now very strong. 

575
00:53:18,663 --> 00:53:22,132
EOWYN:
My lord, your son...

576
00:53:22,132 --> 00:53:24,535
he is dead.

577
00:53:25,903 --> 00:53:27,805
My lord?

578
00:53:28,939 --> 00:53:30,341
Uncle?

579
00:53:36,947 --> 00:53:39,417
Will you not go to him?

580
00:53:42,219 --> 00:53:44,889
Will you do nothing?

581
00:53:44,889 --> 00:53:47,057
Be careful what you say.

582
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:49,427
Do not look for welcome here.

583
00:54:13,250 --> 00:54:17,522
Oh, he must have died
sometime in the night.

584
00:54:17,522 --> 00:54:19,790
What a tragedy
for the king

585
00:54:19,790 --> 00:54:22,727
to lose his only
son and heir.

586
00:54:28,633 --> 00:54:33,671
Especially now that your brother
has deserted you.

587
00:54:33,671 --> 00:54:35,506
Leave me alone, snake!

588
00:54:36,841 --> 00:54:38,609
Oh, but you are alone.

589
00:54:39,844 --> 00:54:44,815
Who knows what you've spoken
to the darkness...

590
00:54:44,815 --> 00:54:48,486
in the bitter watches
of the night...

591
00:54:48,486 --> 00:54:52,390
when all your life
seems to shrink.

592
00:54:52,390 --> 00:54:56,694
The walls of your bower
closing in about you.

593
00:54:56,694 --> 00:55:01,599
A hutch to trammel
some wild thing in.

594
00:55:03,734 --> 00:55:05,703
So fair.

595
00:55:06,871 --> 00:55:08,406
So cold.

596
00:55:09,774 --> 00:55:12,309
Like a morning
of pale spring

597
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:15,913
still clinging
to winter's chill.

598
00:55:29,460 --> 00:55:32,329
Your words are poison.

599
00:55:36,467 --> 00:55:39,770
[***]

600
00:57:04,555 --> 00:57:07,424
You'll find more cheer
in a graveyard.

601
00:57:20,037 --> 00:57:21,238
Ah.

602
00:57:21,238 --> 00:57:24,274
I cannot allow you before
Theoden King so armed,

603
00:57:24,274 --> 00:57:25,576
Gandalf Greyhame.

604
00:57:26,677 --> 00:57:29,580
By order of Grima Wormtongue.

605
00:57:46,697 --> 00:57:48,666
Your staff.

606
00:57:51,769 --> 00:57:55,640
You would not part an old man
from his walking stick.

607
00:58:14,024 --> 00:58:17,194
My lord,
Gandalf the Grey is coming.

608
00:58:25,302 --> 00:58:26,904
He's a herald of woe.

609
00:58:26,904 --> 00:58:32,610
The courtesy of your hall
is somewhat lessened of late,

610
00:58:32,610 --> 00:58:34,244
Theoden King.

611
00:58:34,244 --> 00:58:38,282
He's not welcome.

612
00:58:38,282 --> 00:58:43,621
Why should I welcome you

613
00:58:43,621 --> 00:58:47,792
Gandalf Stormcrow?

614
00:58:47,792 --> 00:58:51,395
A just question, my liege.

615
00:58:51,395 --> 00:58:54,164
Late is the hour

616
00:58:54,164 --> 00:58:58,468
in which this conjurer
chooses to appear.

617
00:58:58,468 --> 00:59:01,405
Lathspell I name him.

618
00:59:01,405 --> 00:59:04,474
Ill news is an ill guest.

619
00:59:04,474 --> 00:59:05,710
Be silent.

620
00:59:05,710 --> 00:59:09,079
Keep your forked tongue
behind your teeth.

621
00:59:09,079 --> 00:59:11,148
I have not passed
through fire and death

622
00:59:11,148 --> 00:59:14,785
to bandy crooked words
with a witless worm.

623
00:59:16,120 --> 00:59:17,755
His staff.

624
00:59:17,755 --> 00:59:20,991
I told you to take
the wizard's staff.

625
00:59:25,329 --> 00:59:27,732
Theoden,

626
00:59:27,732 --> 00:59:30,601
son of Thengel,

627
00:59:31,969 --> 00:59:34,772
too long have you sat
in the Shadows.

628
00:59:37,474 --> 00:59:40,778
I would stay still
if I were you.

629
00:59:40,778 --> 00:59:43,180
Hearken to me!

630
00:59:48,485 --> 00:59:50,755
I release you

631
00:59:50,755 --> 00:59:52,990
from the spell.

632
00:59:54,391 --> 00:59:56,927
[LAUGHS]

633
01:00:04,368 --> 01:00:07,471
You have no power here,

634
01:00:07,471 --> 01:00:11,241
Gandalf the Grey.

635
01:00:16,613 --> 01:00:21,852
I will draw you, Saruman,
as poison is drawn from a wound.

636
01:00:31,161 --> 01:00:32,797
Wait.

637
01:00:33,931 --> 01:00:38,068
SARUMAN'S VOICE:
If I go, Theoden dies.

638
01:00:39,336 --> 01:00:40,871
You did not kill me,

639
01:00:40,871 --> 01:00:43,240
you will not kill him.

640
01:00:47,144 --> 01:00:48,979
Rohan is mine.

641
01:00:50,247 --> 01:00:51,816
Be gone.

642
01:01:35,960 --> 01:01:38,295
I know your face.

643
01:01:42,733 --> 01:01:44,168
Eowyn.

644
01:01:46,403 --> 01:01:47,872
Eowyn.

645
01:01:55,780 --> 01:01:57,081
Gandalf?

646
01:01:57,081 --> 01:02:00,785
Breathe the free air again,
my friend.

647
01:02:13,831 --> 01:02:16,767
Dark have been
my dreams of late.

648
01:02:20,404 --> 01:02:24,574
Your fingers would remember
their old strength better

649
01:02:24,574 --> 01:02:27,812
if they grasped your sword.

650
01:03:09,519 --> 01:03:11,155
Ah, ah!

651
01:03:12,656 --> 01:03:14,791
I've only...

652
01:03:14,791 --> 01:03:17,962
...ever served you, my lord.

653
01:03:17,962 --> 01:03:20,730
Your leechcraft would
have had me crawling

654
01:03:20,730 --> 01:03:23,233
on all fours like a beast!

655
01:03:24,034 --> 01:03:26,170
Send me not from your sight.

656
01:03:28,172 --> 01:03:30,941
No, my lord! No, my lord.

657
01:03:30,941 --> 01:03:32,342
Let him go.

658
01:03:32,342 --> 01:03:35,812
Enough blood has been spilt
on his account.

659
01:03:37,781 --> 01:03:40,317
Get out of my way!

660
01:03:42,452 --> 01:03:45,589
Hail, Theoden King!

661
01:04:10,114 --> 01:04:12,917
Where is Theodred?

662
01:04:15,719 --> 01:04:18,488
Where is my son?

663
01:04:22,059 --> 01:04:24,061
Simbelmyne.

664
01:04:28,765 --> 01:04:32,636
Ever has it grown on the tombs
of my forebearers.

665
01:04:36,306 --> 01:04:39,476
Now it shall cover the grave
of my son.

666
01:04:41,411 --> 01:04:46,116
Alas that these evil days
should be mine.

667
01:04:46,116 --> 01:04:50,887
The young perish
and the old linger.

668
01:04:51,755 --> 01:04:53,323
That I should live

669
01:04:53,323 --> 01:04:57,094
to see the last days
of my house.

670
01:04:58,028 --> 01:05:02,166
Theodred's death
was not of your making.

671
01:05:04,734 --> 01:05:08,505
No parent should have to bury
their child.

672
01:05:25,055 --> 01:05:26,957
He was strong in life.

673
01:05:28,125 --> 01:05:31,928
His spirit will find its way
to the halls of your fathers.

674
01:05:41,571 --> 01:05:44,208
[SPEAKING ROHIRRIM]

675
01:06:16,173 --> 01:06:18,175
They had no warning.

676
01:06:18,175 --> 01:06:21,111
They were unarmed.

677
01:06:21,111 --> 01:06:23,080
Now the Wild Men
are moving through the Westfold,

678
01:06:23,080 --> 01:06:24,414
burning as they go.

679
01:06:26,116 --> 01:06:28,518
Rick, cot and tree.

680
01:06:28,518 --> 01:06:29,586
Where is Mama?

681
01:06:29,586 --> 01:06:30,587
Shh.

682
01:06:30,587 --> 01:06:33,257
This is but a taste
of the terror

683
01:06:33,257 --> 01:06:35,659
that Saruman will unleash.

684
01:06:35,659 --> 01:06:40,430
All the more potent for he is
driven now by fear of Sauron.

685
01:06:41,865 --> 01:06:45,402
Ride out and meet him head-on.

686
01:06:45,402 --> 01:06:49,473
Draw him away
from your women and children.

687
01:06:49,473 --> 01:06:50,940
You must fight.

688
01:06:50,940 --> 01:06:55,145
You have 2000 good men riding
north as we speak.

689
01:06:55,145 --> 01:06:56,813
Eomer is loyal to you.

690
01:06:56,813 --> 01:06:59,683
His men will return
and fight for their king.

691
01:06:59,683 --> 01:07:04,088
They will be 300 leagues
from here by now.

692
01:07:07,357 --> 01:07:09,593
Eomer cannot help us.

693
01:07:09,593 --> 01:07:11,995
I know what it is
you want of me

694
01:07:11,995 --> 01:07:15,665
but I will not bring further
death to my people.

695
01:07:17,101 --> 01:07:19,169
I will not risk open war.

696
01:07:20,870 --> 01:07:24,641
Open war is upon you, whether
you would risk it or not.

697
01:07:28,778 --> 01:07:30,380
When last I looked

698
01:07:30,380 --> 01:07:34,618
Theoden, not Aragorn,
was king of Rohan.

699
01:07:39,256 --> 01:07:41,191
[BELCHES]

700
01:07:41,191 --> 01:07:43,727
Then what is the king's
decision?

701
01:07:49,133 --> 01:07:50,667
 By order of the king 

702
01:07:50,667 --> 01:07:52,336
the city must empty.

703
01:07:53,237 --> 01:07:56,373
We make for the refuge
of Helm's Deep.

704
01:07:56,373 --> 01:07:58,708
Do not burden yourself
with treasures.

705
01:07:58,708 --> 01:08:00,677
Take only what
provisions you need.

706
01:08:00,677 --> 01:08:02,212
Helm's Deep.

707
01:08:02,212 --> 01:08:03,880
They flee to the mountains

708
01:08:03,880 --> 01:08:05,749
when they should
stand and fight.

709
01:08:05,749 --> 01:08:07,884
Who will defend them if not
their king?

710
01:08:07,884 --> 01:08:10,587
He's only doing what he thinks
is best for his people.

711
01:08:10,587 --> 01:08:12,556
Helm's Deep has saved them
in the past.

712
01:08:12,556 --> 01:08:14,358
There is no way out
of that ravine.

713
01:08:14,358 --> 01:08:16,626
Theoden is walking into a trap.

714
01:08:16,626 --> 01:08:19,062
He thinks he's leading
them to safety.

715
01:08:19,062 --> 01:08:21,498
What they will get
is a massacre.

716
01:08:22,666 --> 01:08:25,369
Theoden has a strong will,
but I fear for him.

717
01:08:25,369 --> 01:08:29,506
I fear for the survival
of Rohan.

718
01:08:29,506 --> 01:08:32,976
He will need you
before the end, Aragorn.

719
01:08:32,976 --> 01:08:36,213
The people of Rohan
will need you.

720
01:08:36,213 --> 01:08:39,249
The defenses have to hold.

721
01:08:40,350 --> 01:08:42,386
They will hold.

722
01:08:46,122 --> 01:08:48,525
The Grey Pilgrim.

723
01:08:48,525 --> 01:08:51,361
That's what they
used to call me.

724
01:08:51,361 --> 01:08:54,063
Three hundred lives of Men
I've walked this earth,

725
01:08:54,063 --> 01:08:56,700
and now I have no time.

726
01:08:58,134 --> 01:09:00,370
With luck, my search
will not be in vain.

727
01:09:00,370 --> 01:09:04,241
Look to my coming at first light
on the fifth day.

728
01:09:04,241 --> 01:09:07,877
At dawn, look to the east.

729
01:09:07,877 --> 01:09:09,613
Go.

730
01:09:12,182 --> 01:09:14,251
[***]

731
01:09:45,715 --> 01:09:47,484
You have some skill
with a blade.

732
01:09:56,260 --> 01:09:58,462
Women of this country
learned long ago:

733
01:09:58,462 --> 01:10:01,265
Those without swords
can still die upon them.

734
01:10:01,265 --> 01:10:03,400
I fear neither death nor pain.

735
01:10:04,368 --> 01:10:06,736
What do you fear, my lady?

736
01:10:09,973 --> 01:10:11,841
A cage.

737
01:10:12,876 --> 01:10:16,946
To stay behind bars until use
and old age accept them.

738
01:10:16,946 --> 01:10:18,315
And all chance

739
01:10:18,315 --> 01:10:21,285
of valor has gone
beyond recall or desire.

740
01:10:24,354 --> 01:10:26,623
You're a daughter of kings,

741
01:10:27,624 --> 01:10:31,261
a shieldmaiden of Rohan.

742
01:10:36,266 --> 01:10:38,968
I do not think
that would be your fate.

743
01:10:48,945 --> 01:10:52,582
[***]

744
01:11:12,035 --> 01:11:15,339
 Theoden will not 
 stay at Edoras. 

745
01:11:15,339 --> 01:11:17,541
It's vulnerable. He knows this.

746
01:11:17,541 --> 01:11:20,777
He will expect an attack
on the city.

747
01:11:21,778 --> 01:11:25,315
They will flee to Helm's Deep

748
01:11:25,315 --> 01:11:27,684
the great fortress of Rohan.

749
01:11:27,684 --> 01:11:31,421
WORMTONGUE:
 It is a dangerous road to take 

750
01:11:31,421 --> 01:11:33,490
 through the mountains. 

751
01:11:34,624 --> 01:11:36,493
 They will be slow. 

752
01:11:36,493 --> 01:11:40,797
They will have women
and children with them.

753
01:11:45,134 --> 01:11:47,637
Send out your Warg-riders.

754
01:12:02,085 --> 01:12:05,054
Hey, stinker, don't go getting
too far ahead.

755
01:12:05,054 --> 01:12:06,923
Why do you do that?

756
01:12:06,923 --> 01:12:07,991
What?

757
01:12:07,991 --> 01:12:10,927
Call him names.
Run him down all the time.

758
01:12:10,927 --> 01:12:13,397
Because.

759
01:12:14,631 --> 01:12:16,866
Because that's
what he is, Mr. Frodo.

760
01:12:16,866 --> 01:12:19,135
There's naught left in him
but lies and deceit.

761
01:12:19,135 --> 01:12:22,472
It's the Ring he wants.
It's all he cares about.

762
01:12:22,472 --> 01:12:25,074
You have no idea what
it did to him...

763
01:12:25,074 --> 01:12:27,677
...what it's still doing to him.

764
01:12:29,646 --> 01:12:32,081
I want to help him, Sam.

765
01:12:32,081 --> 01:12:33,550
Why?

766
01:12:38,522 --> 01:12:41,825
Because I have to believe
he can come back.

767
01:12:45,829 --> 01:12:48,064
You can't save him, Mr. Frodo.

768
01:12:48,064 --> 01:12:49,866
What do you know about it?

769
01:12:49,866 --> 01:12:50,967
Nothing!

770
01:12:57,641 --> 01:13:02,879
I'm sorry, Sam. I don't know
why I said that.

771
01:13:02,879 --> 01:13:04,047
I do.

772
01:13:06,015 --> 01:13:08,384
It's the Ring.

773
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:10,119
You can't take your eyes off it.

774
01:13:10,119 --> 01:13:12,656
I've seen you.

775
01:13:12,656 --> 01:13:17,026
You're not eating.
You barely sleep.

776
01:13:18,662 --> 01:13:20,797
It's taken hold
of you, Mr. Frodo.

777
01:13:20,797 --> 01:13:21,798
You have to fight it.

778
01:13:21,798 --> 01:13:23,867
I know what I have to do, Sam.

779
01:13:23,867 --> 01:13:27,103
The Ring was entrusted to me.
It's my task.

780
01:13:27,103 --> 01:13:29,005
Mine! My own!

781
01:13:29,005 --> 01:13:32,408
Can't you hear yourself?

782
01:13:32,408 --> 01:13:34,978
Don't you know who
you sound like?

783
01:13:44,020 --> 01:13:46,255
We wants it.

784
01:13:46,255 --> 01:13:49,158
We needs it.

785
01:13:49,158 --> 01:13:54,130
Must have the precious.

786
01:13:54,130 --> 01:13:57,601
They stole it from us.

787
01:13:57,601 --> 01:14:01,170
Sneaky little Hobbitses.

788
01:14:01,170 --> 01:14:05,308
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

789
01:14:05,308 --> 01:14:08,645
No. Not master.

790
01:14:08,645 --> 01:14:12,649
Yes, precious. False.

791
01:14:12,649 --> 01:14:17,521
They will cheat you,
hurt you, lie!

792
01:14:18,354 --> 01:14:20,824
Master's my friend.

793
01:14:20,824 --> 01:14:26,195
You don't have any friends.
Nobody likes you.

794
01:14:27,330 --> 01:14:29,833
Not listening.
I'm not listening.

795
01:14:29,833 --> 01:14:34,170
You're a liar and a thief.

796
01:14:34,170 --> 01:14:35,705
No.

797
01:14:37,173 --> 01:14:40,143
Murderer.

798
01:14:42,478 --> 01:14:43,580
Go away.

799
01:14:43,580 --> 01:14:46,115
Go away?

800
01:14:48,117 --> 01:14:51,087
I hate you.

801
01:14:51,087 --> 01:14:53,289
I hate you.

802
01:14:53,289 --> 01:14:57,226
Where would you be without me?
Gollum. Gollum.

803
01:14:57,226 --> 01:14:59,228
I saved us.

804
01:14:59,228 --> 01:15:00,664
It was me.

805
01:15:00,664 --> 01:15:03,933
We survived because of me.

806
01:15:05,034 --> 01:15:08,772
Not anymore.

807
01:15:09,773 --> 01:15:11,708
What did you say?

808
01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:17,513
Master looks after us now.

809
01:15:17,513 --> 01:15:21,117
We don't need you.

810
01:15:22,151 --> 01:15:23,452
What?

811
01:15:23,452 --> 01:15:25,388
Leave now,

812
01:15:25,388 --> 01:15:29,392
and never come back.

813
01:15:29,392 --> 01:15:30,794
No.

814
01:15:30,794 --> 01:15:35,231
Leave now and never come back.

815
01:15:37,601 --> 01:15:43,840
Leave now and never come back!

816
01:15:55,551 --> 01:15:58,454
We told him to go away.

817
01:15:58,454 --> 01:16:01,557
And away he goes, precious.

818
01:16:01,557 --> 01:16:03,693
Gone! Gone! Gone!

819
01:16:03,693 --> 01:16:05,829
Smeagol is free!

820
01:16:10,433 --> 01:16:12,001
Look.

821
01:16:12,001 --> 01:16:16,806
Look. See what Smeagol finds?

822
01:16:26,215 --> 01:16:27,651
They are young.

823
01:16:27,651 --> 01:16:30,219
They are tender. They are nice.

824
01:16:30,219 --> 01:16:34,157
Yes, they are.
Eat them. Eat them!

825
01:16:36,660 --> 01:16:38,594
You'll make him sick,
you will,

826
01:16:39,495 --> 01:16:41,931
behaving like that.

827
01:16:44,000 --> 01:16:46,870
There's only one way to eat
a brace of coneys.

828
01:16:46,870 --> 01:16:49,806
[GOLLUM SQUEALING]

829
01:16:50,707 --> 01:16:52,441
What's it doing?

830
01:16:52,441 --> 01:16:55,745
Stupid, fat Hobbit.

831
01:16:55,745 --> 01:16:58,281
It ruins it.

832
01:16:58,281 --> 01:16:59,348
What's to ruin?

833
01:16:59,348 --> 01:17:02,051
There's hardly any meat on them.

834
01:17:02,852 --> 01:17:04,921
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

835
01:17:05,889 --> 01:17:08,825
What we need
is a few good taters.

836
01:17:09,659 --> 01:17:12,628
What's taters, precious?

837
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:14,497
What's taters? Eh?

838
01:17:14,497 --> 01:17:16,232
Po-ta-toes.

839
01:17:16,232 --> 01:17:20,003
Boil them, mash them,
stick them in a stew.

840
01:17:21,537 --> 01:17:27,076
Lovely, big, golden chips
with a nice piece of fried fish.

841
01:17:28,044 --> 01:17:30,246
Even you couldn't
say no to that.

842
01:17:30,246 --> 01:17:32,749
Oh, yes, we could.

843
01:17:32,749 --> 01:17:36,352
Spoil a nice fish.

844
01:17:37,553 --> 01:17:40,389
Give it to us raw,

845
01:17:40,389 --> 01:17:43,559
and wriggling.

846
01:17:43,559 --> 01:17:47,630
You keep nasty chips.

847
01:17:47,630 --> 01:17:49,866
You're hopeless.

848
01:18:02,278 --> 01:18:03,947
Mr. Frodo?

849
01:18:21,597 --> 01:18:24,467
SAM:
Who are they?
Wicked Men.

850
01:18:24,467 --> 01:18:26,936
Servants of Sauron.

851
01:18:26,936 --> 01:18:29,973
They are called to Mordor.

852
01:18:29,973 --> 01:18:33,142
The Dark One is gathering
all armies to him.

853
01:18:33,142 --> 01:18:36,746
it won't be long now.
He will soon be ready.

854
01:18:37,947 --> 01:18:39,648
Ready to do what?

855
01:18:39,648 --> 01:18:41,617
To make his war.

856
01:18:41,617 --> 01:18:47,156
The last war that will cover
all the world in Shadow.

857
01:18:47,156 --> 01:18:48,657
We've got to get moving.

858
01:18:48,657 --> 01:18:50,559
Come on, Sam.

859
01:18:50,559 --> 01:18:52,328
Mr. Frodo.

860
01:18:52,328 --> 01:18:54,063
Look.

861
01:18:57,533 --> 01:19:00,003
It's an oliphaunt.

862
01:19:07,944 --> 01:19:11,180
No one at home
will believe this.

863
01:19:22,225 --> 01:19:24,127
Smeagol?

864
01:20:00,864 --> 01:20:02,065
Ah!

865
01:20:04,233 --> 01:20:07,003
We've lingered here too long.

866
01:20:09,973 --> 01:20:11,274
Come on, Sam.

867
01:20:27,690 --> 01:20:29,926
Bind their hands.

868
01:20:38,567 --> 01:20:41,504
It's true, you don't see
many Dwarf women.

869
01:20:41,504 --> 01:20:45,374
And in fact, they are so alike
in voice and appearance

870
01:20:45,374 --> 01:20:48,844
that they're often mistaken
for Dwarf men.

871
01:20:48,844 --> 01:20:51,114
It's the beards.

872
01:20:51,114 --> 01:20:53,349
This, in turn, has given rise
to the belief

873
01:20:53,349 --> 01:20:56,385
that there are no Dwarf women

874
01:20:56,385 --> 01:21:00,990
and that Dwarves just spring out
of holes in the ground,

875
01:21:02,325 --> 01:21:04,427
which is, of course, ridiculous.

876
01:21:10,299 --> 01:21:13,069
It's all right. Nobody panic.

877
01:21:13,069 --> 01:21:16,205
That was deliberate.
It was deliberate.

878
01:21:34,290 --> 01:21:39,195
ARWEN: The light of the Evenstar 
 does not wax and wane. 

879
01:21:39,195 --> 01:21:42,966
 It is mine to give 
 to whom I will. 

880
01:21:44,633 --> 01:21:47,136
 Like my heart. 

881
01:21:48,504 --> 01:21:51,374
 Go to sleep. 

882
01:21:51,374 --> 01:21:53,977
I am asleep.

883
01:22:00,183 --> 01:22:02,318
This is a dream.

884
01:22:04,520 --> 01:22:07,656
Then it is a good dream.

885
01:22:19,668 --> 01:22:21,971
Sleep.

886
01:22:46,729 --> 01:22:48,497
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

887
01:23:24,733 --> 01:23:26,669
Arwen...

888
01:24:16,051 --> 01:24:18,087
Where is she?

889
01:24:24,860 --> 01:24:28,197
 Our time here is ending. 

890
01:24:28,197 --> 01:24:31,667
Arwen's time is ending.

891
01:24:31,667 --> 01:24:32,801
Let her go.

892
01:24:32,801 --> 01:24:34,970
Let her take the ship
into the west.

893
01:24:34,970 --> 01:24:38,341
Let her bear away her love
for you to the Undying Lands.

894
01:24:38,341 --> 01:24:40,409
There it will be ever green.

895
01:24:41,810 --> 01:24:44,247
But never more than memory.

896
01:24:45,314 --> 01:24:48,484
I will not leave my daughter
here to die.

897
01:24:48,484 --> 01:24:50,953
She stays because
she still has hope.

898
01:24:50,953 --> 01:24:52,321
She stays for you.

899
01:24:52,321 --> 01:24:54,757
She belongs with her people.

900
01:24:59,828 --> 01:25:01,630
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

901
01:25:10,373 --> 01:25:12,441
Why are you saying this?

902
01:25:13,876 --> 01:25:17,246
I am mortal. You are Elf-kind.

903
01:25:19,848 --> 01:25:22,818
It was a dream, Arwen.

904
01:25:22,818 --> 01:25:24,520
Nothing more.

905
01:25:33,196 --> 01:25:35,264
This belongs to you.

906
01:25:37,866 --> 01:25:39,568
It was a gift.

907
01:25:42,070 --> 01:25:43,706
Keep it.

908
01:25:46,108 --> 01:25:47,476
My lord?

909
01:25:50,112 --> 01:25:52,215
She is sailing
to the Undying Lands

910
01:25:52,215 --> 01:25:54,750
with all that
is left of her kin.

911
01:26:18,140 --> 01:26:19,708
What is it?

912
01:26:20,976 --> 01:26:21,977
Hama?

913
01:26:21,977 --> 01:26:23,479
I'm not sure.

914
01:26:39,795 --> 01:26:41,864
Wargs!

915
01:26:54,277 --> 01:26:56,245
A scout!

916
01:27:01,884 --> 01:27:03,218
What is it? What do you see?

917
01:27:03,218 --> 01:27:05,220
Warg! We're under attack!

918
01:27:06,188 --> 01:27:08,557
Get them out of here!

919
01:27:13,128 --> 01:27:15,298
All riders to the head
of the column.

920
01:27:15,298 --> 01:27:18,066
Come on. Get me up here.
I'm a rider.

921
01:27:18,066 --> 01:27:19,835
Come on!

922
01:27:31,514 --> 01:27:34,216
You must lead the people
to Helm's Deep, and make haste.

923
01:27:34,216 --> 01:27:35,784
I can fight.
No!

924
01:27:38,354 --> 01:27:40,589
You must do this, for me.

925
01:27:42,391 --> 01:27:44,393
Follow me!

926
01:27:47,496 --> 01:27:49,532
Forward. I mean, charge forward.

927
01:27:49,532 --> 01:27:52,100
Make for the lower ground!

928
01:27:52,100 --> 01:27:53,736
That's it! Go on!

929
01:27:53,736 --> 01:27:54,837
Stay together!

930
01:29:06,575 --> 01:29:09,011
Bring your pretty face to my ax.

931
01:29:11,647 --> 01:29:13,516
That one counts as mine!

932
01:29:30,065 --> 01:29:31,767
Stinking creature.

933
01:30:58,987 --> 01:31:00,923
Aragorn!

934
01:31:05,460 --> 01:31:07,162
Aragorn?

935
01:31:12,334 --> 01:31:14,737
[SHARKU LAUGHS]

936
01:31:17,072 --> 01:31:18,106
[COUGHS]

937
01:31:18,106 --> 01:31:19,474
[LAUGHING AND GRUNTING]

938
01:31:20,843 --> 01:31:23,411
Tell me what happened
and I will ease your passing.

939
01:31:23,411 --> 01:31:24,947
He's...

940
01:31:24,947 --> 01:31:25,981
[COUGHS]

941
01:31:25,981 --> 01:31:26,982
dead.

942
01:31:28,717 --> 01:31:31,219
He took a little tumble
off the cliff.

943
01:31:34,923 --> 01:31:36,291
You lie.

944
01:31:36,291 --> 01:31:39,027
[LAUGHING AND CHOKING]

945
01:32:09,925 --> 01:32:11,860
Get the wounded on horses.

946
01:32:13,495 --> 01:32:16,031
The wolves of Isengard
will return.

947
01:32:16,031 --> 01:32:17,165
Leave the dead.

948
01:32:25,540 --> 01:32:27,109
Come.

949
01:32:37,620 --> 01:32:39,287
WOMAN 1: At last!
WOMAN 2: Helm's Deep.

950
01:32:39,287 --> 01:32:42,625
WOMAN 3:
There it is, Helm's Deep.

951
01:32:44,827 --> 01:32:46,895
WOMAN 4:
We're safe!

952
01:32:48,296 --> 01:32:49,364
We're safe,

953
01:32:49,364 --> 01:32:51,333
my lady.

954
01:32:51,333 --> 01:32:52,701
Thank you.

955
01:32:53,636 --> 01:32:58,140
[***]

956
01:33:37,345 --> 01:33:38,446
Mama!
MORWEN: Eothain!

957
01:33:38,446 --> 01:33:40,082
Freda!

958
01:33:44,152 --> 01:33:48,190
GAMLING:
Make way for Theoden.
Make way for the king.

959
01:33:55,898 --> 01:33:59,167
So few. So few of you
have returned.

960
01:34:02,504 --> 01:34:04,940
Our people are safe.

961
01:34:06,008 --> 01:34:08,643
We have paid for it
with many lives.

962
01:34:09,477 --> 01:34:10,679
My lady.

963
01:34:14,717 --> 01:34:17,252
Lord Aragorn...

964
01:34:17,252 --> 01:34:18,653
where is he?

965
01:34:20,455 --> 01:34:22,090
He fell.

966
01:34:44,446 --> 01:34:47,549
THEODEN:
Draw all our forces
behind the wall.

967
01:34:47,549 --> 01:34:50,685
Bar the gate.
And set a watch on the surround.

968
01:34:50,685 --> 01:34:53,055
GAMLING:
What of those
who cannot fight, my lord?

969
01:34:53,055 --> 01:34:54,256
The women and children?

970
01:34:54,256 --> 01:34:56,491
THEODEN:
Get them into the caves.

971
01:34:57,492 --> 01:34:59,862
Saruman's arm will
have grown long indeed

972
01:34:59,862 --> 01:35:02,765
if he thinks
he can reach us here.

973
01:35:04,399 --> 01:35:08,070
WORMTONGUE:
 Helm's Deep has one weakness. 

974
01:35:08,070 --> 01:35:10,472
 Its outer wall is solid rock, 

975
01:35:10,472 --> 01:35:13,876
 but for a small culvert 
 at its base, 

976
01:35:13,876 --> 01:35:16,912
 which is little more 
 than a drain. 

977
01:35:19,581 --> 01:35:23,852
How? How can fire
undo stone?

978
01:35:23,852 --> 01:35:28,490
What kind of device
could bring down the wall?

979
01:35:31,994 --> 01:35:36,131
If the wall is breached,
Helm's Deep will fall.

980
01:35:36,131 --> 01:35:38,000
Even if it is breached,

981
01:35:38,000 --> 01:35:39,868
it would take
a number beyond reckoning,

982
01:35:39,868 --> 01:35:42,670
thousands,
to storm the Keep.

983
01:35:42,670 --> 01:35:44,139
Tens of thousands.

984
01:35:44,139 --> 01:35:47,042
But, my lord,
there is no such force.

985
01:35:47,042 --> 01:35:49,311
[HORNS SOUNDING]

986
01:35:49,311 --> 01:35:51,446
[ARMY CHEERING]

987
01:36:00,355 --> 01:36:03,558
A new power is rising.

988
01:36:03,558 --> 01:36:06,761
Its victory is at hand.

989
01:36:12,300 --> 01:36:14,502
This night...

990
01:36:14,502 --> 01:36:19,107
the land will be stained
with the blood of Rohan!

991
01:36:19,107 --> 01:36:22,710
March to Helm's Deep!

992
01:36:22,710 --> 01:36:26,314
Leave none alive!

993
01:36:28,716 --> 01:36:31,319
To war!

994
01:36:35,057 --> 01:36:39,828
There will be no dawn for Men.

995
01:36:56,778 --> 01:36:58,947
Look. There's smoke
to the south.

996
01:36:58,947 --> 01:37:02,250
There is always
smoke rising

997
01:37:02,250 --> 01:37:06,521
from Isengard
these days.

998
01:37:06,521 --> 01:37:08,356
Isengard?

999
01:37:08,356 --> 01:37:10,192
There was a time

1000
01:37:10,192 --> 01:37:14,096
when Saruman would walk
in my woods.

1001
01:37:14,096 --> 01:37:18,300
But now he has
a mind of metal

1002
01:37:18,300 --> 01:37:21,269
and wheels.

1003
01:37:21,269 --> 01:37:26,008
He no longer cares
for growing things.

1004
01:37:26,008 --> 01:37:27,275
What is it?

1005
01:37:27,275 --> 01:37:29,577
[DISTANT HORN SOUNDING
AND FEET MARCHING]

1006
01:37:32,847 --> 01:37:35,150
It's Saruman's army.

1007
01:37:35,150 --> 01:37:37,019
The war has started.

1008
01:37:51,699 --> 01:37:55,103
[***]

1009
01:38:14,856 --> 01:38:19,561
ARWEN:
 May the grace of the Valar 
 protect you. 

1010
01:38:51,759 --> 01:38:53,996
Brego.

1011
01:39:19,787 --> 01:39:21,156
Arwen.

1012
01:39:22,224 --> 01:39:24,292
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1013
01:39:30,832 --> 01:39:32,667
I have made my choice.

1014
01:39:39,007 --> 01:39:42,110
He is not coming back.

1015
01:39:43,245 --> 01:39:46,848
Why do you linger here
when there is no hope?

1016
01:39:46,848 --> 01:39:50,652
There is still hope.

1017
01:39:54,556 --> 01:39:58,593
If Aragorn survives this war,
you will still be parted.

1018
01:40:01,696 --> 01:40:04,799
If Sauron is defeated
and Aragorn made king,

1019
01:40:04,799 --> 01:40:07,535
and all that you hope for
comes true,

1020
01:40:07,535 --> 01:40:12,540
you will still have to taste
the bitterness of mortality.

1021
01:40:12,540 --> 01:40:15,877
Whether by the sword
or the slow decay of time,

1022
01:40:15,877 --> 01:40:19,013
Aragorn will die.

1023
01:40:21,483 --> 01:40:24,286
 And there will be 
 no comfort for you, 

1024
01:40:24,286 --> 01:40:28,656
 no comfort to ease the pain 
 of his passing. 

1025
01:40:31,293 --> 01:40:34,028
 He will come to death, 

1026
01:40:34,028 --> 01:40:36,831
 an image of the splendor 
 of the kings of Men, 

1027
01:40:36,831 --> 01:40:41,769
 in glory undimmed before 
 the breaking of the world. 

1028
01:40:50,845 --> 01:40:55,450
 But you, my daughter... 

1029
01:40:55,450 --> 01:41:00,622
 you will linger on in darkness 
 and in doubt, 

1030
01:41:00,622 --> 01:41:05,093
 as nightfall in winter 
 that comes without a star. 

1031
01:41:07,195 --> 01:41:09,664
 Here you will dwell, 

1032
01:41:09,664 --> 01:41:14,802
 bound to your grief 
 under the fading trees... 

1033
01:41:16,371 --> 01:41:18,506
 until all the world is changed 

1034
01:41:18,506 --> 01:41:20,308
 and the long years of your life 

1035
01:41:20,308 --> 01:41:23,311
are utterly spent.

1036
01:41:31,753 --> 01:41:33,087
Arwen.

1037
01:41:39,394 --> 01:41:42,564
There is nothing
for you here,

1038
01:41:42,564 --> 01:41:44,632
only death.

1039
01:43:02,410 --> 01:43:04,846
 [GALADRIEL SPEAKING IN ELVISH] 

1040
01:43:06,481 --> 01:43:08,850
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

1041
01:43:17,859 --> 01:43:21,696
GALADRIEL:
 The power of the enemy 
 is growing. 

1042
01:43:21,696 --> 01:43:24,532
 Sauron will use his puppet, 
 Saruman 

1043
01:43:24,532 --> 01:43:28,270
 to destroy 
 the people of Rohan. 

1044
01:43:30,137 --> 01:43:33,841
 Isengard has been unleashed. 

1045
01:43:37,879 --> 01:43:41,583
 The Eye of Sauron 
 now turns to Gondor, 

1046
01:43:42,484 --> 01:43:45,620
 the last free kingdom of Men. 

1047
01:43:45,620 --> 01:43:50,358
 His war on this country 
 will come swiftly. 

1048
01:43:53,728 --> 01:43:56,931
 He senses the Ring is close. 

1049
01:43:56,931 --> 01:44:00,635
 The strength of the Ring-bearer 
 is failing. 

1050
01:44:00,635 --> 01:44:04,906
 In his heart, 
 Frodo begins to understand 

1051
01:44:06,341 --> 01:44:10,378
the quest will claim his life.

1052
01:44:10,378 --> 01:44:13,180
You know this.

1053
01:44:13,180 --> 01:44:16,250
 You have foreseen it. 

1054
01:44:18,119 --> 01:44:21,723
 It is the risk we all took. 

1055
01:44:25,993 --> 01:44:27,829
 In the gathering dark, 

1056
01:44:27,829 --> 01:44:29,997
 the will of the Ring 
 grows strong. 

1057
01:44:31,299 --> 01:44:35,803
 It works hard now to find its 
 way back into the hands of Men. 

1058
01:44:35,803 --> 01:44:41,343
 Men, who are so easily seduced 
 by its power. 

1059
01:44:41,343 --> 01:44:45,112
 The young captain of Gondor 
 has but to extend his hand, 

1060
01:44:45,112 --> 01:44:49,617
 take the Ring for his own, 
 and the world will fall. 

1061
01:44:51,919 --> 01:44:53,721
 It is close now. 

1062
01:44:53,721 --> 01:44:58,360
 So close to achieving its goal. 

1063
01:45:01,028 --> 01:45:04,866
 For Sauron will have dominion 
 over all life on this Earth, 

1064
01:45:04,866 --> 01:45:09,371
 even unto to the ending 
 of the world. 

1065
01:45:11,038 --> 01:45:13,074
 The time of the Elves... 

1066
01:45:13,074 --> 01:45:15,710
 is over. 

1067
01:45:15,710 --> 01:45:19,581
 Do we leave Middle-earth 
 to its fate? 

1068
01:45:21,315 --> 01:45:24,752
 Do we let them stand alone? 

1069
01:45:28,790 --> 01:45:30,091
What news?

1070
01:45:30,091 --> 01:45:33,628
Our scouts report Saruman
has attacked Rohan.

1071
01:45:33,628 --> 01:45:36,664
Theoden's people have fled
to Helm's Deep.

1072
01:45:36,664 --> 01:45:38,833
But we must look
to our own borders.

1073
01:45:38,833 --> 01:45:40,835
Faramir,
Orcs are on the move.

1074
01:45:40,835 --> 01:45:43,237
Sauron is marshaling
an army.

1075
01:45:43,237 --> 01:45:45,807
Easterlings and Southrons
are at the Black Gate.

1076
01:45:45,807 --> 01:45:46,841
How many?

1077
01:45:46,841 --> 01:45:49,577
Some thousands.
More come every day.

1078
01:45:50,478 --> 01:45:51,813
Who's covering the river
to the north?

1079
01:45:51,813 --> 01:45:54,048
We pulled 500 men
at Osgiliath.

1080
01:45:54,048 --> 01:45:57,519
If their city is attacked,
we won't hold it.

1081
01:45:59,387 --> 01:46:01,889
Saruman attacks
from Isengard.

1082
01:46:01,889 --> 01:46:04,659
Sauron from Mordor.

1083
01:46:05,693 --> 01:46:09,230
The fight will come to Men
on both fronts.

1084
01:46:09,230 --> 01:46:10,865
Gondor is weak.

1085
01:46:10,865 --> 01:46:14,769
Sauron will strike us soon.

1086
01:46:14,769 --> 01:46:16,771
And he will strike hard.

1087
01:46:16,771 --> 01:46:21,476
He knows now we do not have
the strength to repel him.

1088
01:46:35,022 --> 01:46:37,525
My men tell me
that you are Orc spies.

1089
01:46:37,525 --> 01:46:40,261
Spies?! Now wait just a minute.

1090
01:46:40,261 --> 01:46:42,864
Well, if you're not spies,
then who are you?

1091
01:46:49,771 --> 01:46:50,838
Speak.

1092
01:46:52,440 --> 01:46:55,209
We are Hobbits
of the Shire.

1093
01:46:55,209 --> 01:46:58,546
Frodo Baggins is my name,
and this is Samwise Gamgee.

1094
01:46:58,546 --> 01:47:00,014
Your bodyguard?

1095
01:47:00,014 --> 01:47:02,484
His gardener.

1096
01:47:02,484 --> 01:47:05,019
And where is your
skulking friend?

1097
01:47:06,420 --> 01:47:08,823
That gangrel creature.

1098
01:47:08,823 --> 01:47:11,125
He had an ill-favored look.

1099
01:47:12,694 --> 01:47:14,061
There was no other.

1100
01:47:18,700 --> 01:47:21,168
We set out from Rivendell
with seven companions.

1101
01:47:24,438 --> 01:47:26,941
One we lost in Moria...

1102
01:47:28,576 --> 01:47:30,111
two were my kin,

1103
01:47:30,111 --> 01:47:34,048
a Dwarf there was also.
And an Elf and two Men.

1104
01:47:34,048 --> 01:47:36,651
Aragorn, son of Arathorn,
and Boromir of Gondor.

1105
01:47:43,190 --> 01:47:44,992
You're a friend of Boromir?

1106
01:47:47,328 --> 01:47:48,930
Yes.

1107
01:47:49,997 --> 01:47:51,065
For my part.

1108
01:47:57,271 --> 01:48:00,642
It will grieve you then
to learn that he is dead.

1109
01:48:02,476 --> 01:48:04,178
Dead?

1110
01:48:04,178 --> 01:48:06,147
How? When?

1111
01:48:06,147 --> 01:48:09,150
As one of his companions,
I'd hoped you would tell me.

1112
01:48:14,789 --> 01:48:16,824
He was my brother.

1113
01:48:36,010 --> 01:48:38,012
Captain Faramir!

1114
01:48:39,046 --> 01:48:41,549
[WHISPERING]
We found the third one.

1115
01:48:47,521 --> 01:48:49,691
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1116
01:48:52,860 --> 01:48:55,062
You must come with me. Now.

1117
01:49:06,273 --> 01:49:07,541
Down there.

1118
01:49:22,089 --> 01:49:25,159
To enter the Forbidden Pool
bears the penalty of death.

1119
01:49:35,670 --> 01:49:37,271
They wait for my command.

1120
01:49:42,644 --> 01:49:43,911
Shall I shoot?

1121
01:49:45,813 --> 01:49:48,282
* The rock and pool
Is nice and cool *

1122
01:49:48,282 --> 01:49:50,652
* So juicy sweet *

1123
01:49:50,652 --> 01:49:53,755
* Our only wish
To catch a fish *

1124
01:49:53,755 --> 01:49:56,724
* So juicy sweet **

1125
01:50:00,094 --> 01:50:01,328
[YELLS]

1126
01:50:02,329 --> 01:50:04,065
Wait.

1127
01:50:06,467 --> 01:50:09,804
This creature is bound to me.

1128
01:50:09,804 --> 01:50:11,939
And I to him.

1129
01:50:15,176 --> 01:50:16,610
He is our guide.

1130
01:50:21,215 --> 01:50:22,650
Please...

1131
01:50:22,650 --> 01:50:24,752
let me go down to him.

1132
01:50:32,026 --> 01:50:33,294
[GRUNTS]

1133
01:50:35,963 --> 01:50:37,364
Smeagol.

1134
01:50:37,364 --> 01:50:38,499
[SPITS]

1135
01:50:38,499 --> 01:50:40,902
Master is here.

1136
01:50:42,069 --> 01:50:43,170
Come, Smeagol.

1137
01:50:45,873 --> 01:50:48,776
Trust master. Come.

1138
01:50:51,713 --> 01:50:55,717
We must go now?

1139
01:50:55,717 --> 01:50:59,553
Smeagol, you must trust master.

1140
01:50:59,553 --> 01:51:01,088
Follow me. Come on.

1141
01:51:02,256 --> 01:51:03,925
Come.

1142
01:51:06,327 --> 01:51:07,895
Come, Smeagol.

1143
01:51:07,895 --> 01:51:10,531
Nice Smeagol. That's it.

1144
01:51:10,531 --> 01:51:12,166
Come on.

1145
01:51:13,701 --> 01:51:15,169
[FOOTSTEP]

1146
01:51:16,503 --> 01:51:17,504
Don't hurt him!

1147
01:51:17,504 --> 01:51:18,873
[YELLING]

1148
01:51:18,873 --> 01:51:21,275
Smeagol, don't struggle.
Smeagol, listen to me.

1149
01:51:21,275 --> 01:51:22,744
Master!

1150
01:51:25,379 --> 01:51:27,081
[MUFFLED CRIES]

1151
01:51:33,788 --> 01:51:35,723
No! No!

1152
01:51:37,792 --> 01:51:39,326
[GRUNTING
AND PANTING]

1153
01:51:41,695 --> 01:51:43,297
Where are you leading them?

1154
01:51:43,297 --> 01:51:45,666
[CRYING]

1155
01:51:45,666 --> 01:51:48,035
Answer me.

1156
01:51:48,035 --> 01:51:51,438
GOLLUM:
Smeagol.

1157
01:51:51,438 --> 01:51:52,907
[CRYING]

1158
01:51:54,776 --> 01:51:57,044
Why does it cry,

1159
01:51:57,044 --> 01:51:59,781
Smeagol?

1160
01:52:00,782 --> 01:52:03,617
SMEAGOL:
Cruel Men hurts us.

1161
01:52:03,617 --> 01:52:05,853
Master tricksed us.

1162
01:52:07,254 --> 01:52:10,724
GOLLUM:
Of course he did.

1163
01:52:10,724 --> 01:52:14,595
I told you he was tricksy.

1164
01:52:14,595 --> 01:52:17,765
I told you he was false.

1165
01:52:17,765 --> 01:52:20,667
SMEAGOL:
Master is our friend.

1166
01:52:20,667 --> 01:52:23,104
Our friend.

1167
01:52:23,104 --> 01:52:25,372
GOLLUM:
Master betrayed us.

1168
01:52:25,372 --> 01:52:28,709
SMEAGOL:
No. Not its business.

1169
01:52:28,709 --> 01:52:32,113
Leave us alone!

1170
01:52:32,113 --> 01:52:34,748
GOLLUM:
Filthy little Hobbitses!

1171
01:52:34,748 --> 01:52:37,351
They stole it from us!

1172
01:52:37,351 --> 01:52:38,820
SMEAGOL:
No. No.

1173
01:52:38,820 --> 01:52:41,055
What did they steal?

1174
01:52:42,957 --> 01:52:48,462
GOLLUM:
My precious!

1175
01:52:48,462 --> 01:52:50,331
[YELLS]

1176
01:52:51,999 --> 01:52:54,368
We have to
get out of here.

1177
01:52:54,368 --> 01:52:56,370
You go. Go, now.

1178
01:52:58,840 --> 01:53:00,942
You can do it.

1179
01:53:02,076 --> 01:53:03,777
Use the Ring,
Mr. Frodo.

1180
01:53:03,777 --> 01:53:05,779
Just this once.

1181
01:53:05,779 --> 01:53:07,915
Put it on.

1182
01:53:07,915 --> 01:53:10,151
Disappear.

1183
01:53:11,185 --> 01:53:12,253
I can't.

1184
01:53:15,122 --> 01:53:17,524
You were right, Sam.

1185
01:53:18,860 --> 01:53:21,462
You tried to tell me but...

1186
01:53:26,233 --> 01:53:28,369
I'm sorry.

1187
01:53:32,806 --> 01:53:35,877
The Ring's taking me, Sam.

1188
01:53:37,011 --> 01:53:38,880
If I put it on,

1189
01:53:38,880 --> 01:53:41,348
he'll find me.

1190
01:53:42,884 --> 01:53:45,052
He'll see.

1191
01:53:46,253 --> 01:53:48,222
Mr. Frodo...

1192
01:53:52,960 --> 01:53:57,398
So this is the answer
to all the riddles.

1193
01:53:59,366 --> 01:54:02,703
Here in the Wild
I have you,

1194
01:54:02,703 --> 01:54:04,738
two Halflings,

1195
01:54:04,738 --> 01:54:08,075
and a host of Men at my call.

1196
01:54:11,112 --> 01:54:14,916
The Ring of Power
within my grasp.

1197
01:54:24,258 --> 01:54:28,262
A chance for Faramir,
captain of Gondor...

1198
01:54:29,730 --> 01:54:32,967
to show his quality.

1199
01:54:50,151 --> 01:54:53,287
[VOICE OF THE RING
WHISPERING]

1200
01:54:53,287 --> 01:54:55,189
No!

1201
01:54:58,692 --> 01:55:00,094
Stop it!

1202
01:55:00,094 --> 01:55:01,362
Leave him alone.

1203
01:55:02,629 --> 01:55:05,232
Don't you understand?

1204
01:55:06,267 --> 01:55:08,302
He's got to destroy it!

1205
01:55:08,302 --> 01:55:11,838
That's where we're going,
into Mordor.

1206
01:55:11,838 --> 01:55:14,441
To the Mountain of Fire!

1207
01:55:14,441 --> 01:55:17,844
Osgiliath is under attack.
They call for reinforcements.

1208
01:55:17,844 --> 01:55:21,048
SAM:
Please. It's such a burden.

1209
01:55:22,984 --> 01:55:25,252
Will you not help him?

1210
01:55:26,520 --> 01:55:28,990
Captain?

1211
01:55:28,990 --> 01:55:31,392
Prepare to leave.

1212
01:55:36,130 --> 01:55:38,665
The Ring will go to Gondor.

1213
01:55:50,044 --> 01:55:52,513
[DISTANT MARCHING
FOOTSTEPS]

1214
01:55:56,750 --> 01:55:59,086
[***]

1215
01:56:38,925 --> 01:56:41,328
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

1216
01:56:51,705 --> 01:56:52,873
WOMAN: He's alive!

1217
01:56:52,873 --> 01:56:54,341
Where is he?
Where is he?

1218
01:56:54,341 --> 01:56:57,544
Get out of the way!
I'm going to kill him!

1219
01:56:57,544 --> 01:57:01,482
You are the luckiest,
the canniest,

1220
01:57:01,482 --> 01:57:06,253
and the most reckless man
I ever knew.

1221
01:57:06,253 --> 01:57:08,289
Bless you, laddie.

1222
01:57:08,289 --> 01:57:10,291
Gimli, where is the king?

1223
01:57:19,166 --> 01:57:20,367
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1224
01:57:23,904 --> 01:57:25,372
You look terrible.

1225
01:57:52,333 --> 01:57:54,435
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1226
01:58:00,674 --> 01:58:01,842
[DOORS OPENING]

1227
01:58:07,381 --> 01:58:09,183
A great host, you say?

1228
01:58:09,183 --> 01:58:10,884
All Isengard
is emptied.

1229
01:58:10,884 --> 01:58:12,052
How many?

1230
01:58:12,052 --> 01:58:15,656
Ten thousand strong
at least.

1231
01:58:17,090 --> 01:58:18,559
Ten thousand?

1232
01:58:18,559 --> 01:58:21,562
It is an army bred
for a single purpose:

1233
01:58:24,097 --> 01:58:26,433
To destroy the world of Men.

1234
01:58:28,635 --> 01:58:30,837
They will be here by nightfall.

1235
01:58:36,710 --> 01:58:38,145
Let them come!

1236
01:58:39,346 --> 01:58:42,283
I want every man and strong lad
able to bear arms

1237
01:58:42,283 --> 01:58:45,586
to be ready for battle
by nightfall.

1238
01:58:48,689 --> 01:58:50,123
[HAMMERING]

1239
01:58:50,123 --> 01:58:52,193
MAN: Cross brace.

1240
01:58:53,594 --> 01:58:56,230
We will cover the causeway
and the gate from above.

1241
01:58:56,230 --> 01:58:59,366
No army has ever breached
the Deeping Wall

1242
01:58:59,366 --> 01:59:01,902
or set foot
inside the Hornburg!

1243
01:59:02,769 --> 01:59:04,938
This is no rabble
of mindless Orcs.

1244
01:59:04,938 --> 01:59:07,574
These are Uruk-hai.

1245
01:59:07,574 --> 01:59:11,345
Their armour is thick
and their shields broad.

1246
01:59:12,646 --> 01:59:16,517
I have fought many wars,
Master Dwarf.

1247
01:59:16,517 --> 01:59:20,387
I know how to defend
my own keep.

1248
01:59:26,693 --> 01:59:30,331
They will break upon this
fortress like water on rock.

1249
01:59:30,331 --> 01:59:32,866
Saruman's hordes
will pillage and burn.

1250
01:59:32,866 --> 01:59:35,902
We've seen it before.

1251
01:59:35,902 --> 01:59:38,772
Crops can be resown,

1252
01:59:38,772 --> 01:59:42,243
homes rebuilt.

1253
01:59:42,243 --> 01:59:45,178
Within these walls...

1254
01:59:45,178 --> 01:59:46,747
we will outlast them.

1255
01:59:46,747 --> 01:59:49,383
They do not come to destroy
Rohan's crops or villages.

1256
01:59:49,383 --> 01:59:51,184
They come to destroy
its people,

1257
01:59:51,184 --> 01:59:52,453
down to the last child.

1258
01:59:54,455 --> 01:59:57,023
What would you have me do?

1259
01:59:57,023 --> 01:59:58,725
Look at my men.

1260
01:59:58,725 --> 02:00:00,727
Their courage hangs
by a thread.

1261
02:00:02,896 --> 02:00:04,631
If this is to be our end,

1262
02:00:04,631 --> 02:00:07,334
then I would have them
make such an end

1263
02:00:07,334 --> 02:00:10,571
as to be worthy
of remembrance.

1264
02:00:14,074 --> 02:00:16,142
Send out riders,
my lord.

1265
02:00:16,142 --> 02:00:19,346
You must call for aid.

1266
02:00:22,349 --> 02:00:25,085
And who will come?

1267
02:00:25,085 --> 02:00:26,920
Elves?

1268
02:00:26,920 --> 02:00:29,590
Dwarves?

1269
02:00:29,590 --> 02:00:32,626
We are not so lucky
in our friends as you.

1270
02:00:32,626 --> 02:00:35,696
The old alliances are dead.

1271
02:00:35,696 --> 02:00:38,899
Gondor will answer.
Gondor?!

1272
02:00:38,899 --> 02:00:42,035
Where was Gondor
when the Westfold fell?!

1273
02:00:42,035 --> 02:00:45,739
Where was Gondor when our
enemies closed in around us?!

1274
02:00:45,739 --> 02:00:47,708
Where was Gon--?

1275
02:00:50,243 --> 02:00:52,379
No, my Lord Aragorn...

1276
02:00:53,847 --> 02:00:56,450
we are alone.

1277
02:01:02,923 --> 02:01:04,858
Get the women and children
into the caves.

1278
02:01:04,858 --> 02:01:06,393
We need more time
to lay provisions--

1279
02:01:06,393 --> 02:01:10,230
There is no time.
War is upon us.

1280
02:01:10,230 --> 02:01:11,998
Secure the gate.

1281
02:01:11,998 --> 02:01:14,335
[CAWING]

1282
02:01:17,137 --> 02:01:19,406
We Ents have not troubled

1283
02:01:19,406 --> 02:01:23,009
about the wars
of Men and wizards

1284
02:01:23,009 --> 02:01:26,680
for a very long time.

1285
02:01:27,681 --> 02:01:32,653
But now, something
is about to happen

1286
02:01:32,653 --> 02:01:35,288
that has not happened

1287
02:01:35,288 --> 02:01:37,858
for an age.

1288
02:01:39,025 --> 02:01:41,762
Entmoot.

1289
02:01:41,762 --> 02:01:42,896
What's that?

1290
02:01:42,896 --> 02:01:45,966
'Tis a gathering.

1291
02:01:47,133 --> 02:01:49,770
A gathering of what?

1292
02:01:49,770 --> 02:01:52,806
[RUMBLING]

1293
02:02:07,521 --> 02:02:10,156
Beech. Oak.

1294
02:02:10,156 --> 02:02:12,292
Chestnut. Ash.

1295
02:02:12,292 --> 02:02:14,395
Good. Good. Good.

1296
02:02:14,395 --> 02:02:16,897
Many have come.

1297
02:02:24,337 --> 02:02:27,273
Now we must decide
if the Ents

1298
02:02:27,273 --> 02:02:29,943
will go to war.

1299
02:02:38,685 --> 02:02:41,955
GUARD 1:
Move back! Move to the caves!

1300
02:02:43,023 --> 02:02:45,091
GUARD 1: Keep moving.
GUARD 2: Quickly now.

1301
02:02:51,097 --> 02:02:53,066
[BABY CRYING]

1302
02:02:54,334 --> 02:02:56,503
[***]

1303
02:03:29,169 --> 02:03:31,738
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1304
02:03:39,546 --> 02:03:42,983
Farmers, farriers, stable boys.

1305
02:03:44,017 --> 02:03:45,886
These are no soldiers.

1306
02:03:47,688 --> 02:03:49,656
Most have seen
too many winters.

1307
02:03:49,656 --> 02:03:51,458
Or too few.

1308
02:03:54,995 --> 02:03:58,264
Look at them.
They're frightened.

1309
02:03:58,264 --> 02:03:59,833
You can see it in their eyes.

1310
02:04:05,038 --> 02:04:06,873
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1311
02:04:13,814 --> 02:04:14,815
Aragorn.

1312
02:04:20,587 --> 02:04:22,923
Then I shall die as one of them!

1313
02:04:29,295 --> 02:04:31,297
Let him go, lad.

1314
02:04:31,297 --> 02:04:33,800
Let him be.

1315
02:04:34,968 --> 02:04:37,604
 Every villager 
 able to wield a sword 

1316
02:04:37,604 --> 02:04:40,741
has been sent
to the armoury.

1317
02:04:44,945 --> 02:04:46,880
My lord?

1318
02:04:48,749 --> 02:04:51,585
Who am I, Gamling?

1319
02:04:54,688 --> 02:04:58,825
You are our king, sire.

1320
02:05:01,628 --> 02:05:05,031
And do you trust your king?

1321
02:05:06,466 --> 02:05:09,736
Your men, my lord...

1322
02:05:09,736 --> 02:05:12,773
will follow you
to whatever end.

1323
02:05:19,479 --> 02:05:21,582
To whatever end.

1324
02:05:31,057 --> 02:05:34,861
Where is the horse
and the rider?

1325
02:05:34,861 --> 02:05:38,131
Where is the horn
that was blowing?

1326
02:05:39,332 --> 02:05:44,070
 They have passed like rain 
 on the mountains. 

1327
02:05:44,871 --> 02:05:48,274
 Like wind in the meadow. 

1328
02:05:51,812 --> 02:05:55,548
The days have gone down
in the West...

1329
02:05:56,382 --> 02:05:59,085
 behind the hills... 

1330
02:06:00,821 --> 02:06:02,723
 into Shadow. 

1331
02:06:10,864 --> 02:06:14,635
How did it come to this?

1332
02:06:18,538 --> 02:06:21,675
GUARD:
Move! Move to the outer wall.

1333
02:06:38,925 --> 02:06:40,593
Give me your sword.

1334
02:06:49,770 --> 02:06:51,571
What is your name?

1335
02:06:51,571 --> 02:06:54,074
Haleth, son of Hama, my lord.

1336
02:06:55,976 --> 02:06:58,879
The men are saying
we will not live out the night.

1337
02:07:00,647 --> 02:07:02,816
They say that it is hopeless.

1338
02:07:20,500 --> 02:07:22,202
This is a good sword.

1339
02:07:24,237 --> 02:07:26,707
Haleth, son of Hama...

1340
02:07:30,777 --> 02:07:33,113
there is always hope.

1341
02:07:55,668 --> 02:07:59,505
We have trusted you this far.
You have not led us astray.

1342
02:07:59,505 --> 02:08:01,274
Forgive me.

1343
02:08:01,274 --> 02:08:02,843
I was wrong to despair.

1344
02:08:05,879 --> 02:08:08,414
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1345
02:08:11,818 --> 02:08:14,855
We had time,
I'd get this adjusted.

1346
02:08:17,991 --> 02:08:20,260
It's a little tight
across the chest.

1347
02:08:22,428 --> 02:08:24,130
[HORN SOUNDING]

1348
02:08:26,399 --> 02:08:28,368
That is no Orc horn.

1349
02:08:31,404 --> 02:08:33,073
[HORN SOUNDS]

1350
02:08:33,907 --> 02:08:35,909
Send for the king.

1351
02:08:35,909 --> 02:08:37,110
Open the gate!

1352
02:08:37,110 --> 02:08:39,780
GUARD:
Open up the gate!

1353
02:09:11,144 --> 02:09:13,046
How is this possible?

1354
02:09:13,880 --> 02:09:17,517
I bring word from Elrond
of Rivendell.

1355
02:09:17,517 --> 02:09:21,021
An alliance once existed
between Elves and Men.

1356
02:09:21,021 --> 02:09:26,059
Long ago we fought
and died together.

1357
02:09:28,061 --> 02:09:31,331
We come to honor
that allegiance.

1358
02:09:31,331 --> 02:09:33,166
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

1359
02:09:39,572 --> 02:09:41,507
You are most welcome.

1360
02:09:46,813 --> 02:09:50,984
We are proud to fight
alongside Men once more.

1361
02:10:04,430 --> 02:10:07,200
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

1362
02:10:07,200 --> 02:10:09,402
[INDISTINCT
GRUNTING AND GROWLING]

1363
02:10:24,284 --> 02:10:27,888
GIMLI:
You could have picked
a better spot.

1364
02:10:33,293 --> 02:10:35,028
Well, lad, whatever luck
you live by,

1365
02:10:35,028 --> 02:10:36,963
let's hope it lasts the night.

1366
02:10:37,998 --> 02:10:40,200
[THUNDERCLAP]

1367
02:10:42,869 --> 02:10:44,837
Your friends
are with you, Aragorn.

1368
02:10:44,837 --> 02:10:48,041
Let's hope they last the night.

1369
02:10:51,644 --> 02:10:53,346
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1370
02:11:22,208 --> 02:11:24,644
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS]

1371
02:11:28,781 --> 02:11:31,251
[BABY CRYING]

1372
02:11:47,833 --> 02:11:50,103
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1373
02:11:59,012 --> 02:12:00,513
Ahh!

1374
02:12:29,242 --> 02:12:30,776
What's happening out there?

1375
02:12:30,776 --> 02:12:32,312
Shall I describe it to you?

1376
02:12:33,213 --> 02:12:35,415
Or would you like me
to find you a box?

1377
02:12:58,171 --> 02:13:01,074
[URAK-HAI BATTLE CRIES]

1378
02:13:38,511 --> 02:13:40,413
So it begins.

1379
02:14:07,039 --> 02:14:08,641
Did they hit anything?

1380
02:14:08,641 --> 02:14:11,177
Give them a volley.

1381
02:14:11,177 --> 02:14:12,512
Fire!

1382
02:14:12,512 --> 02:14:13,546
Fire!

1383
02:14:18,751 --> 02:14:21,354
[SPEAKING ELVISH]

1384
02:14:29,028 --> 02:14:31,097
Send them to me! Come on!

1385
02:14:51,617 --> 02:14:52,785
Good!

1386
02:14:59,292 --> 02:15:02,495
Swords! Swords!

1387
02:15:32,325 --> 02:15:34,760
Legolas! Two already!

1388
02:15:34,760 --> 02:15:36,396
I'm on 17!

1389
02:15:36,396 --> 02:15:39,765
Huh?! I'll have no pointy-ear
outscoring me!

1390
02:15:46,306 --> 02:15:48,308
Nineteen!

1391
02:16:13,165 --> 02:16:16,302
[ENTS GROANING]

1392
02:16:25,511 --> 02:16:26,846
Merry.

1393
02:16:29,315 --> 02:16:33,486
We have just agreed.

1394
02:16:41,193 --> 02:16:43,195
Yes?

1395
02:16:43,195 --> 02:16:47,533
I have told your names
to the Entmoot

1396
02:16:48,434 --> 02:16:52,204
and we have agreed

1397
02:16:52,204 --> 02:16:57,142
you are not Orcs.

1398
02:16:57,142 --> 02:16:59,379
Well, that's good news.

1399
02:16:59,379 --> 02:17:00,913
And what about Saruman?

1400
02:17:00,913 --> 02:17:03,616
Have you come
to a decision about him?

1401
02:17:03,616 --> 02:17:07,720
Now, don't be hasty,
Master Meriadoc.

1402
02:17:07,720 --> 02:17:09,922
Hasty?

1403
02:17:10,923 --> 02:17:12,325
Our friends are out there.

1404
02:17:12,325 --> 02:17:16,796
They need our help. They cannot
fight this war on their own.

1405
02:17:16,796 --> 02:17:19,265
War? Yes.

1406
02:17:19,265 --> 02:17:21,834
It affects us all.

1407
02:17:21,834 --> 02:17:26,238
But you must understand,
young Hobbit

1408
02:17:26,238 --> 02:17:28,308
it takes a long time

1409
02:17:28,308 --> 02:17:33,379
to say anything in Old Entish

1410
02:17:33,379 --> 02:17:37,683
and we never say anything

1411
02:17:37,683 --> 02:17:41,954
unless it is worth taking

1412
02:17:41,954 --> 02:17:46,626
a long time to say.

1413
02:17:46,626 --> 02:17:50,229
Seventeen! Eighteen!

1414
02:17:50,229 --> 02:17:51,931
Nineteen!

1415
02:17:51,931 --> 02:17:53,966
Twenty!

1416
02:17:53,966 --> 02:17:55,668
Twenty-one!

1417
02:18:05,745 --> 02:18:07,547
Causeway!

1418
02:18:07,547 --> 02:18:10,483
[ARAGORN SHOUTS IN ELVISH]

1419
02:18:15,388 --> 02:18:17,823
Is this it?

1420
02:18:17,823 --> 02:18:20,960
Is this all you can conjure,
Saruman?

1421
02:19:46,979 --> 02:19:48,581
Brace the gate!

1422
02:20:06,532 --> 02:20:09,034
Hold them! Stand firm!

1423
02:20:16,842 --> 02:20:18,410
Aragorn!

1424
02:20:22,815 --> 02:20:24,083
Gimli!

1425
02:20:30,155 --> 02:20:31,724
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1426
02:21:12,131 --> 02:21:16,902
The Ents cannot
hold back this storm.

1427
02:21:16,902 --> 02:21:21,240
We must weather such things
as we have always done.

1428
02:21:22,241 --> 02:21:24,209
How can that be your decision?!

1429
02:21:24,209 --> 02:21:28,447
This is not our war.

1430
02:21:28,447 --> 02:21:31,016
But you're part of this world!

1431
02:21:35,020 --> 02:21:36,889
Aren't you?!

1432
02:21:38,457 --> 02:21:40,626
[ENTS GRUMBLING]

1433
02:21:40,626 --> 02:21:43,563
You must help. Please.

1434
02:21:44,496 --> 02:21:47,299
You must do something.

1435
02:21:47,299 --> 02:21:52,037
You are young and brave,
Master Merry.

1436
02:21:52,905 --> 02:21:56,842
But your part
in this tale is over.

1437
02:21:56,842 --> 02:21:59,545
Go back to your home.

1438
02:22:09,254 --> 02:22:11,591
Maybe Treebeard's right.

1439
02:22:11,591 --> 02:22:13,626
We don't belong here, Merry.

1440
02:22:13,626 --> 02:22:16,161
It's too big for us.

1441
02:22:16,161 --> 02:22:18,898
What can we do in the end?

1442
02:22:21,133 --> 02:22:24,269
We've got the Shire.

1443
02:22:24,269 --> 02:22:26,906
Maybe we should go home.

1444
02:22:28,574 --> 02:22:31,911
The fires of Isengard
will spread

1445
02:22:31,911 --> 02:22:37,149
and the woods of Tuckborough
and Buckland will burn.

1446
02:22:37,149 --> 02:22:38,951
And...

1447
02:22:40,285 --> 02:22:43,856
And all that was once green and
good in this world will be gone.

1448
02:22:46,959 --> 02:22:50,229
There won't be a Shire, Pippin.

1449
02:23:09,548 --> 02:23:10,850
GAMLING:
Aragorn!

1450
02:23:10,850 --> 02:23:13,485
Fall back to the Keep!

1451
02:23:13,485 --> 02:23:16,789
Get your men out of there!

1452
02:23:17,757 --> 02:23:19,992
[SHOUTS IN ELVISH]

1453
02:23:26,298 --> 02:23:27,667
Haldir!

1454
02:23:31,904 --> 02:23:35,474
What are you doing?
What are you stopping for?

1455
02:23:35,474 --> 02:23:37,009
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1456
02:23:54,493 --> 02:23:55,795
Haldir!

1457
02:23:55,795 --> 02:23:58,330
[***]

1458
02:24:36,501 --> 02:24:38,103
Brace the gate!

1459
02:24:40,806 --> 02:24:42,274
Hold them!

1460
02:24:43,943 --> 02:24:47,412
To the gate. Draw your swords!

1461
02:25:11,303 --> 02:25:13,372
Make way!

1462
02:25:15,975 --> 02:25:17,977
We cannot hold much longer!

1463
02:25:23,749 --> 02:25:24,850
Hold them!

1464
02:25:24,850 --> 02:25:27,552
How long do you need?

1465
02:25:27,552 --> 02:25:30,322
As long as you can give me.

1466
02:25:30,322 --> 02:25:32,057
Gimli!

1467
02:25:33,458 --> 02:25:34,860
Timbers!

1468
02:25:34,860 --> 02:25:37,062
Brace the gate!

1469
02:25:51,676 --> 02:25:53,578
Come on. We can take them.

1470
02:25:53,578 --> 02:25:56,115
It's a long way.

1471
02:26:01,220 --> 02:26:03,889
Toss me.

1472
02:26:03,889 --> 02:26:04,890
What?

1473
02:26:04,890 --> 02:26:05,958
I cannot jump the distance!

1474
02:26:05,958 --> 02:26:07,927
You'll have to toss me!

1475
02:26:13,098 --> 02:26:14,666
Don't tell the Elf.

1476
02:26:14,666 --> 02:26:17,069
Not a word.

1477
02:26:31,951 --> 02:26:33,452
Shore up the door!

1478
02:26:33,452 --> 02:26:35,855
Make way!
Follow me to the barricade.

1479
02:26:35,855 --> 02:26:37,222
Watch our backs!

1480
02:26:41,026 --> 02:26:42,527
Throw another one over here!

1481
02:26:42,527 --> 02:26:43,528
Higher!

1482
02:27:33,178 --> 02:27:34,914
Hold fast the gate!

1483
02:27:38,884 --> 02:27:42,154
Gimli! Aragorn!
Get out of there!

1484
02:27:46,625 --> 02:27:48,427
Aragorn!

1485
02:28:21,660 --> 02:28:24,496
Pull everybody back.

1486
02:28:24,496 --> 02:28:26,498
Pull them back.

1487
02:28:26,498 --> 02:28:28,500
Fall back!

1488
02:28:28,500 --> 02:28:31,103
Fall back!

1489
02:28:32,037 --> 02:28:33,905
They have broken through!

1490
02:28:33,905 --> 02:28:36,475
The castle is breached. Retreat!

1491
02:28:36,475 --> 02:28:38,577
Fall back!
Retreat!

1492
02:28:38,577 --> 02:28:41,613
ARAGORN:
Hurry! Inside. Get them inside!

1493
02:28:41,613 --> 02:28:44,016
GAMLING:
Into the Keep!

1494
02:28:55,194 --> 02:29:00,299
I will leave you at the western
borders of the forest.

1495
02:29:00,299 --> 02:29:05,370
You can make your way north
to your homeland from there.

1496
02:29:10,842 --> 02:29:12,978
Wait! Stop!

1497
02:29:12,978 --> 02:29:14,679
Stop!

1498
02:29:17,682 --> 02:29:20,185
Turn around.

1499
02:29:20,185 --> 02:29:21,786
Turn around. Take us south.

1500
02:29:21,786 --> 02:29:23,088
South?

1501
02:29:23,088 --> 02:29:28,227
But that will lead you
past Isengard.

1502
02:29:28,227 --> 02:29:31,230
Yes. Exactly.

1503
02:29:31,230 --> 02:29:34,566
If we go south, we can slip
past Saruman unnoticed.

1504
02:29:34,566 --> 02:29:37,436
The closer we are to danger,
the farther we are from harm.

1505
02:29:37,436 --> 02:29:39,738
It's the last thing
he'll expect.

1506
02:29:42,107 --> 02:29:45,477
That doesn't make sense to me.

1507
02:29:45,477 --> 02:29:46,745
But then

1508
02:29:46,745 --> 02:29:49,648
you are very small.

1509
02:29:49,648 --> 02:29:51,583
Perhaps you're right.

1510
02:29:53,985 --> 02:29:55,720
South it is, then.

1511
02:29:56,988 --> 02:30:00,592
Hold on, little Shirelings.

1512
02:30:02,294 --> 02:30:05,264
I always like going south.

1513
02:30:05,264 --> 02:30:09,834
Somehow it feels
like going downhill.

1514
02:30:09,834 --> 02:30:12,871
Are you mad? We'll be caught.

1515
02:30:12,871 --> 02:30:15,607
No, we won't.

1516
02:30:15,607 --> 02:30:18,143
Not this time.

1517
02:30:24,549 --> 02:30:25,684
Look!

1518
02:30:27,086 --> 02:30:29,754
Osgiliath burns!

1519
02:30:29,754 --> 02:30:31,423
Mordor has come.

1520
02:30:32,224 --> 02:30:34,859
The Ring will not save Gondor.

1521
02:30:35,827 --> 02:30:38,497
It has only
the power to destroy.

1522
02:30:38,497 --> 02:30:40,465
Please,

1523
02:30:40,465 --> 02:30:42,601
let me go.

1524
02:30:43,635 --> 02:30:45,304
Hurry.

1525
02:30:48,573 --> 02:30:50,041
Faramir!

1526
02:30:50,041 --> 02:30:52,577
You must let me go!

1527
02:30:52,577 --> 02:30:56,448
And those little family
of field mice

1528
02:30:56,448 --> 02:30:59,918
that climb up sometimes,
and they tickle me awfully.

1529
02:30:59,918 --> 02:31:03,054
They're always trying
to get somewhere where they--

1530
02:31:03,054 --> 02:31:05,724
Oh.

1531
02:31:14,499 --> 02:31:18,203
Many of these trees
were my friends.

1532
02:31:18,203 --> 02:31:23,142
Creatures I had known
from nut and acorn.

1533
02:31:24,075 --> 02:31:25,344
I'm sorry, Treebeard.

1534
02:31:25,344 --> 02:31:28,480
They had voices of their own.

1535
02:31:30,549 --> 02:31:33,285
Saruman.

1536
02:31:33,285 --> 02:31:36,655
A wizard should know better!

1537
02:31:38,290 --> 02:31:41,460
[TREEBEARD ROARS]

1538
02:31:50,569 --> 02:31:54,439
There is no curse in Elvish,

1539
02:31:54,439 --> 02:31:57,309
Entish or the tongues of Men

1540
02:31:57,309 --> 02:31:59,844
for this treachery.

1541
02:32:05,217 --> 02:32:07,819
with rock and stone.

1542
02:32:07,819 --> 02:32:11,756
[GROANING
AND FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1543
02:32:31,876 --> 02:32:33,278
Yes.

1544
02:32:34,346 --> 02:32:35,714
Come, my friends.

1545
02:32:36,881 --> 02:32:41,152
The Ents are going to war.

1546
02:32:41,152 --> 02:32:43,121
It is likely

1547
02:32:43,121 --> 02:32:46,858
that we go to our doom.

1548
02:32:48,059 --> 02:32:50,762
Last march

1549
02:32:50,762 --> 02:32:53,298
of the Ents.

1550
02:33:41,012 --> 02:33:43,214
Faramir! Orcs have taken
the eastern shore.

1551
02:33:43,214 --> 02:33:45,116
Their numbers are too great.

1552
02:33:45,116 --> 02:33:47,486
By nightfall we will be overrun.

1553
02:33:49,988 --> 02:33:51,623
Mr. Frodo?

1554
02:33:51,623 --> 02:33:55,827
It's calling to him, Sam.
His Eye is almost on me.

1555
02:33:55,827 --> 02:33:58,730
Hold on, Mr. Frodo.
You'll be all right.

1556
02:34:00,965 --> 02:34:06,237
[MUTED SPEECH]

1557
02:34:12,877 --> 02:34:14,413
Take them to my father.

1558
02:34:15,647 --> 02:34:18,983
Tell him Faramir
sends a mighty gift.

1559
02:34:20,985 --> 02:34:25,156
A weapon that will change our
fortunes in this war.

1560
02:34:25,156 --> 02:34:28,627
Do you want to know
what happened to Boromir?

1561
02:34:28,627 --> 02:34:31,796
You want to know
why your brother died?

1562
02:34:31,796 --> 02:34:33,798
He tried to take
the Ring from Frodo,

1563
02:34:33,798 --> 02:34:35,934
after swearing an oath
to protect him!

1564
02:34:35,934 --> 02:34:38,002
He tried to kill him!

1565
02:34:38,002 --> 02:34:40,405
The Ring drove your brother mad!

1566
02:34:40,405 --> 02:34:43,274
ITHILIEN RANGER:
Watch out!

1567
02:34:53,885 --> 02:34:55,320
Mr. Frodo?

1568
02:34:57,522 --> 02:34:59,691
They're here.

1569
02:35:02,461 --> 02:35:05,163
They've come.

1570
02:35:05,163 --> 02:35:07,699
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHING]

1571
02:35:07,699 --> 02:35:09,734
Nazgul!

1572
02:35:31,523 --> 02:35:33,958
Stay here. Keep out of sight.

1573
02:35:35,494 --> 02:35:37,996
Take cover!

1574
02:35:55,146 --> 02:35:57,416
The fortress is taken.

1575
02:35:57,416 --> 02:35:58,717
It is over.

1576
02:35:58,717 --> 02:36:00,652
You said this fortress
would never fall

1577
02:36:00,652 --> 02:36:03,154
while your men defend it.

1578
02:36:03,154 --> 02:36:06,057
They still defend it.
They have died defending it.

1579
02:36:08,527 --> 02:36:10,361
WOMAN 1:
They're breaking in!

1580
02:36:12,564 --> 02:36:15,467
WOMAN 2:
They're past the door!

1581
02:36:18,236 --> 02:36:20,439
Is there no other way
for the women and children

1582
02:36:20,439 --> 02:36:22,807
to get out of the caves?

1583
02:36:25,276 --> 02:36:27,512
Is there no other way?

1584
02:36:31,883 --> 02:36:34,953
But they will not get far.
The Uruk-hai are too many.

1585
02:36:39,524 --> 02:36:40,825
Send word for the women
and children

1586
02:36:40,825 --> 02:36:42,193
to make for the mountain pass.

1587
02:36:42,193 --> 02:36:43,895
And barricade the entrance!

1588
02:36:43,895 --> 02:36:45,396
So much death.

1589
02:36:47,031 --> 02:36:50,869
What can Men do
against such reckless hate?

1590
02:36:55,273 --> 02:36:56,941
Ride out with me.

1591
02:37:00,712 --> 02:37:02,547
Ride out and meet them.

1592
02:37:02,547 --> 02:37:05,049
For death and glory.

1593
02:37:05,049 --> 02:37:07,151
For Rohan.

1594
02:37:08,419 --> 02:37:10,154
For your people.

1595
02:37:10,154 --> 02:37:12,857
The sun is rising.

1596
02:37:16,961 --> 02:37:18,429
GANDALF:
 Look to my coming 

1597
02:37:18,429 --> 02:37:20,298
 at first light 
 on the fifth day. 

1598
02:37:20,298 --> 02:37:21,733
 At dawn, 

1599
02:37:21,733 --> 02:37:23,802
 look to the east. 

1600
02:37:27,872 --> 02:37:29,674
Yes.

1601
02:37:31,943 --> 02:37:33,678
Yes.

1602
02:37:34,746 --> 02:37:37,415
The horn of Helm Hammerhand

1603
