because how could the end
be happy?

1651
02:45:19,410 --> 02:45:21,912
 How could the world go back 
 to the way it was 

1652
02:45:21,912 --> 02:45:24,015
 when so much bad had happened? 

1653
02:45:24,015 --> 02:45:26,884
Victory!

1654
02:45:26,884 --> 02:45:29,353
We have victory!

1655
02:45:30,721 --> 02:45:35,126
 But in the end, 
 it's only a passing thing, 

1656
02:45:35,126 --> 02:45:36,794
 this shadow. 

1657
02:45:36,794 --> 02:45:39,998
 Even darkness must pass. 

1658
02:45:39,998 --> 02:45:43,034
 A new day will come. 

1659
02:45:43,034 --> 02:45:47,671
 And when the sun shines, 
 it will shine out the clearer. 

1660
02:45:49,207 --> 02:45:51,842
 Those were the stories 
 that stayed with you, 

1661
02:45:51,842 --> 02:45:53,477
 that meant something. 

1662
02:45:53,477 --> 02:45:57,381
 Even if you were too small 
 to understand why. 

1663
02:45:57,381 --> 02:46:01,585
 But I think, Mr. Frodo, 
 I do understand. 

1664
02:46:01,585 --> 02:46:03,021
 I know now. 

1665
02:46:04,088 --> 02:46:06,390
Folk in those stories

1666
02:46:06,390 --> 02:46:10,828
had lots of chances of turning
back, only they didn't.

1667
02:46:10,828 --> 02:46:13,564
They kept going

1668
02:46:13,564 --> 02:46:17,168
because they were holding
on to something.

1669
02:46:18,469 --> 02:46:21,105
What are we holding on to, Sam?

1670
02:46:32,650 --> 02:46:36,954
That there's some good
in this world, Mr. Frodo.

1671
02:46:36,954 --> 02:46:39,657
And it's worth fighting for.

1672
02:47:06,384 --> 02:47:10,988
I think at last we understand
one another, Frodo Baggins.

1673
02:47:10,988 --> 02:47:13,857
You know the laws
of our country,

1674
02:47:13,857 --> 02:47:15,526
